title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions; set aside.
In a baking dish layer repeatedly pudding, wafers and bananas until dish is full or your run out of items.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar; beat a little longer.
Smooth over top of pudding mixture.
Brown to a golden
brown in 350° oven. Same dish can be made only use drained pineapple (crushed type) in place of bananas.
Equally good.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix and pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake covered in oven at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: greek onion salad
directions: Peel and slice onion, tomato and cucumber into thin rounds. Toss and mix in a large salad bowl.
Add oregano, oil and vinegar to taste.
Toss until well mixed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt mary's tea cakes
directions: Sift flour into large bowl.
Round out center and pour in other ingredients.
Mix well with hands, until most of flour is absorbed.
Break off dough in small pieces and roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake about 12 minutes at 400°. Decorate if desired.
Makes about 100 cookies.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: fiesta corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, olives, pimento, onion and green pepper with eggs and seasonings; add cracker crumbs and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crumbly apple pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; stir into apples.
Place in pie shell.
Combine remaining flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: eggplant caviar *(caponata)
directions: Combine eggplant, onion, pepper, mushrooms, garlic and oil in a large skillet.
Cover pan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix all together and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, until eggplant is cooked, but not mushy.
Chill at least overnight or freeze.
To serve, bring to room temperature.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients except sugar.
Prepare carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Combine ground beef, vegetables, soup and juice in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: mocha mousse
directions: Combine sugar, water and coffee in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Place chocolate chips in blender and add sugar syrup.
Blend for 6 seconds.
Add eggs and blend for 1 minute.
Remove from blender and fold mixture into whipped cream. Pour in serving bowls and refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: In blender, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle generously with nutmeg and cinnamon. Bake at 350° until knife inserted halfway between outside and center comes out clean.
(Start checking after 30 minutes.)

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat and onion flakes.
Drain.
Pour into large soup pot.
Add all ingredients, including liquid.
Add 1 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cover and cook on medium heat for a couple of hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: glitter playdough
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, heat and stir until mixture pulls away from sides of pan. Knead and Play!

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with sugar. Add mashed sweet potatoes and mix well.
Mix in butter, shortening, salt and baking powder.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
Dough will be sticky.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Flour hands and knead gently 3 or 4 times.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter or a glass.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening and slowly add sugars, eggs and pumpkin. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda; add alternately with milk to mixture.
Fold in walnuts and extract.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetables garden dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cucumber, radish, dill weed and celery seed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour; just before serving stir in bacon bits.

title: cheese twists
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour and yeast. In a saucepan, heat buttermilk, butter, sugar and salt to 120° to 130°; add to flour mixture.
Blend on low speed until moistened. Add eggs; beat on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 3 minutes. Stir in enough whole wheat flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until nearly doubled, about 1 hour.

title: glenn's corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, carrots and seasonings until done and thick.
Add corn and bacon pieces.
Continue cooking (stirring often).
Turn fire out and add milk.
Stir until completely mixed. (Do not cook after adding milk.)
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: old country store orange dressing
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add extract.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.
Serve on fresh fruit.

title: ms. michon l. crawford's apple butter
directions: Wash apples, quarter and remove stems and seeds.
Cook in large stockpot with vinegar and apple cider until soft.
Put through food mill. Return to stock pot.
Stir in sugar and all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Stir until apples thicken. Reduce heat immediately to low.
To test, place spoonful in saucer to cool.
If mixture does not run or appear watery, apple butter is done.
Place in jars which have been sterilized in the oven. Seal as instructed.

title: vela archer's sour dough bread
directions: Combine 1 cup warm water, sugar, potato flakes.
Stir in yeast that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand for 8-10 hours.
Then refrigerate for 3-5 days.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale. Freeze in ice cubes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together.
Put 1 cup chopped nuts in bottom of a tube pan (greased and floured).
Pour batter on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 65 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, melted butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cream together and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (sift).
Pour in Wesson oil.
Add eggs and beat by hand.
Add grated carrots and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
and bake in covered greased casserole at 350° for
minutes.
You
may
use
diced
chicken, soya meat and extra chopped mushrooms if you like.

title: garden peas in cream
directions: Heat butter and water to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients, except cream.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Cover and simmer until peas are tender, 8 to 15 minutes.
Don't drain.
Add cream.
Serves 4.

title: parslied new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes under cold running water to remove dirt or grit. Cut away any sun spots or scars.
Cut in half (do not peel).
Place in a large kettle of boiling water and cook until tender, but not mushy, about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile combine the butter, parsley, vinegar, salt and pepper in a serving bowl and set aside until needed.
When the potatoes are tender drain them in a colander and skin gently to rid of excess water.
Place potatoes in the prepared serving bowl and toss gently until seasonings are evenly distributed and potatoes are coated.
Serve hot.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Separate into two balls.
Roll out between two pieces of wax paper.
Makes top and bottom pie crust.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and salt; then drain.
Then refrigerate for 2 hours.
Take out and add to green and red peppers, sugar, vinegar, mustard and turmeric.
Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Seal while hot.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: mini pepperoni breads
directions: Thaw dough according to package.
Roll into rectangle shape (approximately 8 x 12-inch).
Spread pepperoni on dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top of pepperoni.
Roll tightly lengthwise.
Slice 1-inch thick pieces.
Place flat on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake until bottom is golden brown at 350°, 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except walnuts. Stir together; add eggs.
Add chopped walnuts, if desired.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cake cool and frost.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cake is done, put on coconut and pecans.

title: cookie crumb pie
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until they form soft peaks.
Add sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts, vanilla and cookies. Spread in buttered pie pan and bake for 35 minutes in a 325° oven. Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry whipped cream cake
directions: Bake angel food cake as directed on package; let cool.
Whip cream; add sugar, then add strained strawberries and Jell-O, partly set.
Beat all together.
Cut cake in 3 layer sections. Spread between layers, then spread all over outside.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours, then serve.

title: frozen strawberry jelly
directions: Mash berries; add sugar.
Stir occasionally and let stand 1/2 hour.
Put Certo in and put in jars and freeze.
Cover jars.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onions together.
Add the fried bacon. Place in uncovered casserole dish.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sauce for cocktail wieners
directions: Simmer in slow cooker for 1 hour or until heated thoroughly.

title: bean dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together in food processor until smooth.

title: grandma lux orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, butter and eggs.
Put soda in sour cream and add to creamed mixture.
Grate the rind of the orange and squeeze the juice.
Add these to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients, gradually add flour until you have a dough for cutting cookies.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aunt hattie's cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice thin.
Place in salt water and ice to crisp for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove ice and press all water out.
Mix dressing (should be consistency of pudding).

title: summer sausage
directions: *Note:
If you use turkey, cut down on water a bit.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Bottle and process 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 pints.
I put my onions and peppers in a food grinder.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Cream plain flour and softened margarine.
Spread in a glass baking dish and sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: avocado orange dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Serve over salad.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Mix together pineapple, lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk, coconut, pecans and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Melt butter and Crisco.
Pour over and mix with sugars, vanilla, baking powder, baking soda, eggs and flour.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over top.
Mix milk, eggs and sugar together.
Pour over apples. Mix Bisquick and brown sugar.
Sprinkle this over the apples and top with sliced butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Use 9-inch pie plate.
Line pie plate.
Cook 1/2 way.
Peel, core and slice tomatoes.
Be sure tomatoes are drained.
Layer pie crust with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Continue to layer with tomatoes, cheese and onions until pie is full. Frost with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Place in 9 x 13 inch greased pan and bake according to directions on box.
Top with topping.

title: pineapple cranberry squares
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, cool, stir in undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce until mixture thickens.
Fold in pecans.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread over jello mixture and chill.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 2 hours, then drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Stir well to mix. Pour over mixture in glass or plastic containers and freeze.
To serve, just thaw.
The pickles will be crispy and tasty.

title: oven-barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces; place meaty side up in a large shallow pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes longer, basting occasionally.

title: sponge cake delight
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease bottom only of two 8-inch cake pans.
Beat egg yolks until light lemon colored.
Add salt, sugar and coffee. Beat well until smooth.
Slowly add the flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold carefully into yolk mix until no white shows.
Divide batter evenly between the two prepared round pans. Smooth out if needed. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Then raise temperature to 375° and continue baking for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Turn out on rack. Place one layer on cake plate.

title: basic one-dish meal
directions: Brown meat (may substitute stew meat).
Drain fat.
Add sauce or soup (may substitute any other soup like mushroom or cheese). Add vegetables.
Cook noodles (any pasta) separately and add. Season to taste.
Many varieties.
All good and healthy.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bones and dice.
Prepare rice according to directions.
Cook onion in butter until tender but not browned.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms and keep liquid.
Add enough chicken broth to liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Add cream; cook and stir until thick.
Add wild rice, mushrooms, chicken, pimento, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel crunchies(try these sugarless candies next time you crave something sweet.)
directions: Cook juice and vinegar to 238° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add almond butter and cereal.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Drop 12 teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
While still warm, but not hardened, form each candy into a square.
Chill until firm.

title: "hello dollies"
directions: Layer cracker crumbs 1/4 to 1/2-inch high in a square 9-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients as listed and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add corn and dry ingredients; pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Test with knife.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and half of Cool Whip. In a large, deep glass dish, punch bowl or salad bowl, make 2 layers with wafers, bananas and mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 10 -12.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until blended, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out onto rack and cool completely.
If desired, dust with confectioners sugar before serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix for two minutes. Place in 2 regular loaf pans or can use five mini loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for one hour (regular loaf) and 45 minutes for mini loaves.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Dissolve 2 packages yeast, water, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour to make a thin paste.
Let rise.
Scald milk.
Let shortening, margarine and Crisco melt in milk to lukewarm.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Knead and let rise until double.
Roll out and make two rectangles.
Spread with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: painted cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla, and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda; add to creamed mixture, stirring until blended.
Shape dough into 2 balls, wrap each in waxed paper and chill 4 hours.

title: pineapple-cream cheese jello
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add gelatin to water; add to pineapple, let cool.
(Put in refrigerator.)

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, eggs, sour cream, flour and vanilla.
Mix
at
low
speed on mixer for 2 minutes. Sprinkle pecans in
bottom
of greased tube pan. Pour half of batter in pan, then
sprinkle
teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon (mixed together) over
batter.
Add remainder of batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together well.
Add the nuts and mini marshmallows to mixture, if you so desire.
Fold the Cool Whip into the mixture.
Freeze in mold or in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Serve frozen or lightly thawed.

title: microwave fruitcake
directions: Cream butter,
sugar
and
corn syrup.	Add eggs 1 at a time, beating continually.
Blend flour, salt, baking powder, nutmeg, allspice
and cinnamon until smooth.
Stir in brandy. Fold in cherries
and
nuts.
Pour into 12 cup Bundt pan (very lightly greased).
Microwave on High for 18 minutes, rotating a quarter turn every 4 minutes.
Rest 15 to 20 minutes before loosening. Invert from pan.
Glaze if desired.

title: meat pies(french)
directions: Put ingredients in a large pot with 3 cups of water over low heat.
Cook slowly to remove pink.
Divide into 4 uncooked pie shells.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Freezes really well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Dice onion, pepper, pimento and olives.
Combine with corn and other ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey cream candy
directions: Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it forms a soft ball in cool water.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup nuts (chopped) and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple and oranges, including juice, in a bowl; add pudding and Tang.
Slice apples and bananas into mixture. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
(Can also add grapes, nuts or fruit cocktail may be used.)

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread out in 2 (9 x 13-inch) bread pans and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares which makes eight (to pan).
Then flour squares and fry until brown on each side.
Then put in baking dishes or bread pans and pour soup and water.
I add a little Kitchen Bouquet to make the gravy brown.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: russian tea 2
directions: Mix all together.
To serve, put 2 teaspoons of tea mixture with 6 ounces of hot water.

title: four egg dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use enough buttermilk to mix ingredients.
Bake as cornbread.

title: tuna 'n rice dinner
directions: Melt butter in large skillet on medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until tender, but not browned.
Stir in vegetables, milk, soup and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with almonds (optional).

title: speedies
directions: Cut the meat into 3/4 inch cubes.
Combine all liquid and spices, and stir.
Add the meat, stir and cover.
Put in refrigerator and marinate overnight.
Cook over grill by placing meat on skewers, eight pieces to a skewer, and baste liberally with left-over marinade sauce.
Best eaten "hot dog" style in Italian bread.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in pecans and parsley.
Freezes well.

title: marinated broiled lamb chops
directions: Mix lemon juice and browning sauce in shallow plastic or stainless steel pan.
Marinate chops for several hours or overnight, turning chops occasionally.
Broil chops about 25 minutes, basting often with juice.
Turn once.
Nice with baked potato or buttered noodles.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn, tossing well.
Spread on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Stir while cooling.
Store in airtight container.

title: salmon newburg
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
In medium saucepan, blend undiluted soup with half and half, thyme and nutmeg.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in small amount of sauce into egg. Add back to sauce; cook 2 minutes.
Fold in green onion, pimento and salmon.
Heat over low heat, about 5 minutes.
Blend in lemon juice and paprika.
Serve over hot rice.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add cocoa and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Serve each slice with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: sweet-hot mustard
directions: Put mustard and vinegar in blender.
Add eggs and sugar. Blend at high speed until frothy.
Pour into double boiler; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Makes approximately 2 cups. Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: baked squash deluxe
directions: Use canned squash or, if fresh, boil until tender.
In separate container, dilute mushroom soup with milk.
Layer ingredients, starting with squash and ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian style chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Mix soy sauce, 1/4 cup wine and next 5 ingredients.
Pour over chicken and marinate several hours, turning occasionally.
Cook onions in 4 tablespoons of butter until golden. Remove onions; remove chicken from marinade.
Dry and sprinkle with flour.
Brown chicken in drippings.
Add onions and marinate. Cover and cook 45 minutes, uncovering pan last 15 minutes.
Cook and drain rice (keep hot).
Brown pineapple slices in 1 tablespoon butter.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each one.
Add vanilla and pinch of salt.
Beat at medium speed until mixed well and very creamy.
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Bring beans to a boil.
Drain and pour into casserole dish. Add soup.
Slice cheese and place over soup.
Top with onions. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain all fruits and combine all ingredients.
Chill.

title: stuffed ricotta eggplant
directions: Wash off eggplant with cold water.
Cut off stem.
Cut and slice eggplant lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
(You will get about 10 to 12 slices with large eggplant.)
Dip slices into well beaten egg mixture, then dip into bread crumbs; shake off excess. Place eggplant slices into greased baking sheet and bake at 325° until golden brown.
Remove; let cool and set aside.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions with salt. Add ice and let stand, covered with weighted lid for 3 hours.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Trim the excess fat off the spareribs and set aside.
In a large dish, mix all the ingredients.
Place the ribs into mixture and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Turn once in a while, while they sit in the mix.
Grease the wire rack in the oven to prevent the ribs from sticking (do this to the top rack).
Place a pan half filled with water under the top rack.
Place the ribs on the greased rack in the oven.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Brush ribs occasionally with the marinade sauce.

title: alexander cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Grind the almonds.
Whip the egg whites in a large mixing bowl until stiff. Fold in the almonds and sugar.
Spread the batter into 2 equal size heart shaped layers on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, make the custard cream; combine the egg yolks, cream, sugar and cornstarch in the top of a double boiler.
Let the custard cream cook slowly over boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until it thickens, stir constantly.
Stir in the rum, then cool.
Frost top of one layer with half the custard cream.
Place the second layer on top and spread with remaining cream.
Garnish with almonds.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sieve the persimmons and add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add sugar and beat again.
Sift flour with salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to persimmon mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites; pour into greased 2-quart dish and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peaches with amaretto
directions: Slice and peel peaches, marinate in Amaretto in shallow glass bowl for 2 hours.
Serve in glass dishes and sprinkle with crumbled cookies.
Serves 4.

title: mother's sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, potato, sherry wine, spices and add melted butter last.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until golden brown and filling is firm.
Serve cold with Cool Whip or whipped cream seasoned with 1 tablespoon sherry.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Fold into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: german cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add milk, dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Mix only until moistened.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan (12 x 17-inch) or whatever will produce a 1 or 2-inch cookie. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with a thin layer of chocolate frosting or coffee frosting while still warm.
Produces a brownie-like cookie.
Christmas is not complete without this one! Yield:
Twenty 2-inch squares.

title: smoked eggs
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, sugar, oil, salt and liquid smoke in small bowl.
Add eggs.
Marinate at room temperature 2 to 3 hours, turning eggs often to keep them evenly coated.
Drain.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 8.
Can leave in sauce in refrigerator for up to 3 days.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, sugar and melted margarine.
Add pineapple.
Beat whipped cream.
Layer with vanilla wafers, like a banana pudding.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Refrigerate.

title: hawaiian delight salad
directions: Soften cream
cheese
with dry jello.
Add marshmallows to 2 cups hot water, then add to jello mixture.	Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill
until
set (slightly thick).	Stir Cool Whip into mixture.
May be used as salad or dessert.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Slice 1 roll of cookie dough and press into a large, greased Pyrex pan.
Spread cream cheese over dough.
Slice second roll of dough and cover cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until dough browns.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream and chill well.
Top with sour cream mixed with a hint of garlic, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and sugar in saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add cream, then eggs, then baking powder.
Make certain dry ingredients are incorporated.
Combine with corn and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: garlic-cheese biscuits
directions: Make biscuits using 2 cups flour; cut in shortening.
Stir in salt and baking powder.
Add enough milk to mix ingredients together.
You can then toss dough onto a floured surface, roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut biscuits (or) form balls of dough and put them on a cookie tray (flatten just a little).
Dot each biscuit with butter, then sprinkle with garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: meatballs with appetizer sauce
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and shape into bite-sized meatballs.
Brown and serve with Appetizer Sauce.

title: sloppy joes dogs
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain pan drippings and stir in tomato sauce, chili powder, steak sauce, salt and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve immediately over frankfurters in buns.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: easy oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter; add mushroom soup, oyster crackers, cheese, sherry and oysters.
Mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/4-quart casserole dish. Top with more cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dirt
directions: Mix pudding as package directs.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients, except Oreos.
Chop Oreos in food processor and alternate layers of pudding and Oreos.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Peel
and
core
apples.
Slice
in quarters, then thin slices.
Put
rest	of ingredients (to taste) in another bowl. Dip in	mixture
corn
bread
or
white bread until soaked and place bread
on
bottom
of pan (13 x 9-inch).
Spoon on apple mixture. Place 2nd piece of bread on top.
Put pan in another pan of water in oven
and
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	Serve with whipped cream.

title: microwave zesty squash
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well-sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup of stuffing mixture into veggie mixture. Turn into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Can be doubled; bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: quick rolls
directions: In a large bowl put cool liquid (scalded milk, salt, shortening and sugar cooled to lukewarm); add dissolved yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Cool.
Add to flour to make a batter.
If dough is not stiff enough to knead, add more flour.
It may take all four cups of flour.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.

title: sesame treats
directions: Cook honey in a heavy bottomed pan until candy reaches 265°. Take off stove.
Then stir in seed well.
Butter a cookie sheet. Then pour mixture and spread evenly.
When hardened, cut into pieces and enjoy.

title: sausage kolaches
directions: In large bowl, mix the water, sugar and yeast.
Then add the lukewarm margarine and Crisco.
Also the beaten eggs.
Then add the dry milk, flour and salt.
Mix until you have a smooth dough. Cover and let rise for about 15 minutes.
Punch down and knead until real smooth again.
Let rise again until double in size. Spoon out dough and wrap it around sausages.
Butter tops and let rise again.
Bake at 375° until browned.
Brush with oleo when done, cover with clean cloth until cool.
Approximately 40 rolls.

title: lemon bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together first five ingredients.
In another bowl, beat together egg, milk, oil and lemon juice.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour batter into two greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.

title: pizza cauliflower
directions: Bring cauliflower to a boil in salt water just until it starts to get soft.
Drain well.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Spoon on tomato soup straight from can.
Place Longhorn cheese on top of soup and top with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano and then plenty of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow mile-high squares
directions: Microwave chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in large microwave safe bowl on Medium-high (70% power) for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth.
Cool for 1 minute.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread into foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 48 squares.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and Eagle Brand milk well.
Add sugar and vanilla and some milk.
Put in ice cream freezer and add the rest of the milk-about 1/2 gallon. Put extra can of pet milk.

title: family bean curd
directions: Heat oil in nonstick pan or wok. When oil is very hot, stir-fry carrot, beans and mushrooms 1 minute. Add bean curd, soy sauce and stock and bring to a boil. Thicken with cornstarch. Sprinkle with chopped green onions and remove to serving dish. Drizzle with sesame oil and serve immediately. Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: far east fruit bars (date)
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then nuts and fruit.
Mix well.

title: tomato-artichoke aspic
directions: Bring 2 cups of vegetable juice to a boil in a medium saucepan; remove from heat and add all of the gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Pour 2 cups of gelatin mixture into an oiled 11-cup ring mold.
Let the remaining juice mixture stand at room temperature.
Chill mixture in mold until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Press artichoke halves into thickened mixture around outside of mold; chill until firm.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crust:
Place 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth over 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Top with rest of mixture, then freeze.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cream or celery soup, sour cream and cream cheese or shredded cheese.
Add to vegetables.
Place in a casserole dish.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put in 2-quart bowl and stir sugar and syrup together. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir in peanuts. Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Remove and add butter and vanilla.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir gently.
Pour quickly into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk together. Roll dough into pizza shape, then spread the sausage over the top.
Roll up and wrap in foil. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: minnesota munchers
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix together vegetable oil, milk, eggs, almond extract and vanilla. Add dry mixture to egg mixture; stir to moisten. Stir in poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noel date cookies
directions: Beat oleo with brown sugar.
Add egg white and beat.
Mix in dry ingredients along with yogurt and vanilla.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost if desired.
Makes 40.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Heat vinegar, salt and sugar to dissolve sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer.

title: shrimp-a-rue
directions: In a large pot, boil 5 quarts water with Old Bay seasoning and onions.
Add potatoes and boil 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn and boil 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove potatoes, sausage and corn with a slotted spoon.
Add shrimp to pot and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp and serve with additional Old Bay seasoning, seafood cocktail sauce and butter. Serves 12.

title: appetizer pizza(wonderful!)
directions: Set your cream cheese out to soften.
Add 3 or 4 tablespoons milk to whip in with cream cheese.
Spread it on a round platter at least 13-inches (like pizza crust).
Spread the jar of cocktail sauce over this.
Layer shrimp then the rest of the ingredients. Serves 15 to 20.

title: chicken salad veronique
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding more soy sauce, if desired.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: barnes' pot roast
directions: Get a large, deep frying pan instead of a roasting pan.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in butter until coarse.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk and egg.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moist. Turn into floured surface and knead lightly until smooth and shape into ball.
Place in large Pyrex bowl.
Cut in a 4-inch cross about 1/4-inch deep.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut fine and layer in this order: lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon.

title: tangy cheese spread
directions: Whip until all ingredients are spreadable.
Chill.
Use on crackers or heavy dipping chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, beat well, add eggs, mix well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients to oil and sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and carrots (a small amount at a time.)
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
For layers bake for 30 minutes.

title: microwave vegetable medley
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in shallow 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with bouillon granules and toss.
Dot with butter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 2 minutes.
Give dish a half turn and cook 2 more minutes on High.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Serves 4.
Can be easily doubled.

title: tuna aloha
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Combine with tuna, parsley, salt, pepper, onion juice, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and white sauce or soup.
Place pineapple slices on shallow baking dish; brush with brown sugar mixture.
Spoon tuna-rice mixture onto pineapple slices, shaping each mound (an ice cream scoop works well).
Sprinkle with dry bread crumbs or crushed cornflakes.
Top each with a large pinch of grated cheese, using remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 5.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg.
Mix together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add flavorings.
Refrigerate for awhile.
Take a teaspoon of dough and roll in palm of hand.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Put glass in sugar and press down dough. Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: hot cranapple punch
directions: Simmer 15 minutes or longer.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slices from each pepper.
Remove all seed and membranes.
Wash inside and outside.
Heat to boiling 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add peppers.
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Lightly stuff pepper with meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add cracker crumbs, pineapple, coconut and baking powder.
Mix well. Add nuts. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: m&m cookie pops
directions: You will need wooden popsicle sticks.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix up Kool-Aid as package directs for 2-quart container.
Pour into punch bowl.
Pour in 1/2 of the soda and 1/2 of the sherbet. This will make 1 punch bowl of juice.
Use the other half of soda and the rest of the sherbet to make a second punch bowl of juice with another 2 quarts of Kool-Aid.

title: prize winning children's cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Quick, easy and good.

title: pasta with no cook tomato sauce(get ready for those garden tomatoes)
directions: Combine Mozzarella, tomatoes, parsley, basil, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Toss gently and set aside for at least 30 minutes.

title: black bean chili
directions: Remove casing from sausage; discard. Crumble sausage into large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook until onion is translucent. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Yields 10 cups.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and press into a 13 1/2 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake until light golden, 12 to 15 minutes. Cool. Drain 1 can pineapple; add enough water to make 1 cup liquid. Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello and let cool until slightly jelled.
Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, pineapple, cottage cheese and topping.
Fold all together into the jello and pour on the crust.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook beef in oven until medium done; slice.
Layer slices in pan.
Combine all ingredients, except beef, and bring to a boil and pour over meat.
Continue cooking meat until very tender, 2 to 4 hours at 300°.
Baste with sauce.
Add more water if sauce gets too thick.
May be prepared ahead and frozen.
Excellent for serving a large group or holiday meal.

title: cayenne toast
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Whisk melted butter and seasoning mixture often.
Saturate bread with mixture.
Bake until hard (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: wassail
directions: Simmer 2 hours or more. Stir occasionally.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, chili powder and garlic powder in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until beef is brown.
Drain off any fat.
Layer on large platter in this order:
lettuce, 1/2 chips, beans, tomatoes and chips.
Heat nacho sauce until very warm. Spoon over salad.
Sprinkle green peppers over sauce.
Enjoy!

title: cheese roll
directions: Let Velveeta sit out until soft.
Place between two sheets of wax paper.
Press down with hands, then using rolling pin, roll out to desired length and width.
Remove top sheet of wax paper. Spread cream cheese evenly on top of cheese.
Spread jalapeno dip out evenly on top of cream cheese.
Then carefully roll up, removing wax paper as you go.
Refrigerate overnight.
Tastes better if eaten the next day.
Serve with crackers.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix well. Pour over steaks. Turn every 15 minutes for
1 hour. Baste with sauce while cooking.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: With mixer, mix sugar, salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Mix slightly.
Add onion flakes and stir in oil slowly.
Continue beating until thick.
Add poppy seed and stir until well blended. Good on cabbage, fruit salad or avocados.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Bring to boil, stirring continuously, marshmallow cream, milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Add nuts and spread into buttered pan.

title: creamy rice bake
directions: Mix Rice-a-Roni, mushroom soup and green beans.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes and onion rings.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Place butter and vanilla in bowl; cream together until smooth. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and continue beating for 1 minute. Add eggs and beat for 30 seconds.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to mixture until thoroughly mixed, about 1 minute.

title: halibut with heavenly topping
directions: Place towel dried fillets, skin side down, in a single layer on well-greased shallow baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Brush tops with lemon juice.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 6 to 8 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Remove fish from heat and spread cheese mixture on fish.
Broil
2 to 3 minutes longer, or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: mexican crock-pot dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Add Ro-Tel, chili, Ranch Style beans and Velveeta.
Simmer in crock-pot at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add 1 carton sour cream.

title: simple pineapple pie
directions: Mix pudding with sour cream; add well drained pineapple.
Pour into crust and chill for a few hours or overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: valjean's drop donuts
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Fry in oil on top of stove in heavy pan until brown. Drain on brown paper bag covered with paper towel.
Roll in either powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix and gelatin.
Add oil, eggs and milk.
When thoroughly mixed, add strawberries, coconut and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool completely before icing.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1 1/2-quarts water or bring water to boil for 5 minutes and then let soak for 2 hours; drain.
Add chicken broth and water to cover and remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti with turkey meatballs
directions: For sauce, in a Dutch oven, cook onion, green pepper, carrot and celery in hot oil until tender.
Stir in fresh or undrained canned tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Bring to boiling; add Turkey Meatballs.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
If necessary, uncover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more or until sauce is desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook pasta and drain.
Arrange pasta on individual plates or a large platter. Spoon the meatballs and sauce over pasta.

title: spinach and noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles following package directions.
Combine all ingredients and pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: peach bavarian salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in hot water.
Drain peaches and add 1 cup liquid to Jell-O.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut peaches into chunks and fold into salad. Chill until firm.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix together and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream butter, sugar and milk.
Alternate a little sugar at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Roll into small pieces and let stand.
Makes about 100 balls, depending on size of ball.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Mix all together.
This will make 2 cups.
Dredge chicken, fish or chops.
Bake in oven.

title: steak aupoivre
directions: Combine vinegar and brown sugar.
Flatten steaks with side of heavy cleaver.
Press 1/2 teaspoon of ground peppercorn into each side of each steak.
Melt butter in skillet and saute steaks 3 to 4 minutes per side in butter.
Pour off fat after removing steaks. Add vinegar and sugar mixture.
Add stock and cream and cook until thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over steaks to serve.
Garnish with slices of lime.
Serve with rice, spinach salad and asparagus.
Makes 2 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Pour into floured, greased tube pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, pepper, salt and hot sauce.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.

title: spiked fruit bowl
directions: Combine water, sherry and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool completely.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large glass bowl.
Pour sherry mixture over fruit; cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yield:
10 servings (80 calories per serving).

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
When reaches a full, rolling boil, turn heat down and boil 5 minutes. Take off heat; add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir well and pour over popcorn.
Put into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans and put into 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Don't let sit in pan to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, cheese, egg and milk.
Drop into hot cooking oil from a spoon.
The hush puppies will float on top when done.
Serve with fried fish.
This recipe is about 60 years old.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: five layer casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, beef,
pepper
and
onions in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test potatoes for doneness in about 50 minutes.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Arrange marshmallows in pan.
In a microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over the marshmallows. Chill completely.
Cut between marshmallows.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan the sugar, flour and salt (cocoa for chocolate).
Measure milk.
Add enough milk to make smooth paste. Beat in 3 egg yolks.
Add remainder of milk and 1/2 stick of oleo. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
(Then 1/2 cup coconut or 1 small sliced banana or 1/2 small can crushed pineapple, well drained.)
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into baked shell and add meringue.
You can also caramelize 1/4 cup of the sugar at the first to make caramel pie.

title: glazed carrots with herbs
directions: Cook the carrots in boiling water for 5 minutes or until al dente.
Drain in a colander and refresh them under cold running water.
Saute in the butter until coated.
Add broth.
Season to taste.
Continue to saute until liquid reduces and glazes.
Stir in the parsley and dill.
Serve immediately.

title: nut sticks
directions: Put ground nuts in frying pan with sugar, egg whites and water; heat until sugar is melted; add flavoring.
Set aside.
Mix flour and butter as you would for pie crust.
Add yeast mixture. Warm milk in small saucepan with 1 tablespoon sugar and crumbled yeast.
Add yolks, salt and more sugar.
Add to flour mixture and mix with hands.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve over greens.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup, evaporated milk and water.
Pour over pork chops and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cool broccoli and noodles.
Combine chicken, sour cream, soup, onion and salt.
Place noodles in greased casserole dish; sprinkle half the cheese on top.
Place broccoli next.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese, then the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked dressing and turkey (or chicken)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except soup.	Use part or all of water depending on how moist you want the dressing.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Thin
soup
with
1/2 cup of water or milk.
Top casserole.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes.
Chopped pimento may be added for flavor and to add color.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Blend flour and shortening.
Add potatoes and blend.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough and knead lightly, using as little flour as possible on bread board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with cutter.
Place biscuits on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter; also good with ham.

title: creamed sauerkraut
directions: Saute onion.
Add sauerkraut and heat it.
Add the cream of mushroom soup (do not dilute).
Mix the sauerkraut and the cream of mushroom soup.
Add the caraway seed (this is optional, however the caraway seed added to the sauerkraut enhances the flavor and also reduces the gas associated with all kinds of cabbage).

title: apricot almond bread
directions: Sift together whole wheat flour, pastry flour and soda.
Chop apricots fine.
Add water, butter, sugar and salt.
Cool, then add other ingredients.
Turn into buttered, floured loaf pan or 2 small pans and bake for 1 1/4 hours (or less) in moderate oven (350°).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Using mixer, put all wet ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients gradually; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2 small or 1 extra large).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and butter until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Spread remainder in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs together; fold in mandarin orange slices.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: one-hour hot rolls
directions: Scald milk; cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Stir in egg; add to Bisquick mix.
Beat well but quickly, until ball of soft dough is formed.
Turn onto lightly floured, cloth covered board.
Knead gently for 1/2 minute.
Roll out into circle, 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes for rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise in warm, moist place until double in bulk, or about 40 minutes.
Bake in moderate hot oven (375°) for 15 minutes.
Makes 18 average size rolls.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Knead peanut butter, butter, sugar, dates and nuts thoroughly. Press into logs 2-inches long, using 1 tablespoon mixture for each. Place on waxed paper and chill overnight.
Melt chocolate and wax in top of double boiler.
Insert a cake tester or hat pin through the end of each log; dip in chocolate and let any excess drip. Place on cookie sheet until firm.

title: super mexican casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased or Pammed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with tortillas.
Brown meat with onion, chili powder, salt and pepper. Drain and spread over tortillas.
Next, layer beans; do not drain. Slice and layer cheese over beans.
Cover with remaining tortillas. Combine soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with a wire whisk until well blended about 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in olive oil and garlic (or steam, if you prefer) in large frypan.
Stir in cooked pasta.
Add butter over low heat.
Add Parmesan and stir until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
If you prefer, you may add half and half or evaporated milk to create a creamy sauce.
Feel free to change vegetables to suit your taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, but not well done. Mix soup and sour cream. Add squash, onions and carrots. Put half stuffing in baking pan. Pour squash mixture over it and place remainder of the stuffing on top. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour and salt in a paper bag.
Drop in beef, a portion at a time, and shake until coated.
In a heavy kettle or pot, brown beef over low heat in hot oil.
Stir water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are done.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add all ingredients together and pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in olive oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place chicken breasts over the vegetables.
Combine tomato sauce and seasonings and pour over the chicken.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Serve over spaghetti, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Remove seeds and chop cucumbers.
Mix with remainder of ingredients (except white bread).
Spread thin layer of butter on bread, then cucumber mixture.
Remove crust; cut diagonal into triangles.
Place in freezer 30 minutes, then place in refrigerator before serving.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In an electric skillet, melt oleo. Add onion and paprika. Place cut up chicken in skillet and cook for 30 minutes at 250°. Turn chicken and cook for 30 minutes more. Remove chicken and add soft sour cream to remaining onion mixture. Place chicken back into the skillet and once again, cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: garlic parmesan eggplant slices
directions: Place eggplant slices on 10 x 15 x 1 jelly roll pan; sprinkle with salt.
In 9-inch pie pan, stir together flour, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and basil.
In 10-inch skillet cook olive oil, pepper and garlic over medium that until sizzling.
Meanwhile, dip eggplant slices into eggs; coat with flour mixture.
Fry 1/2 of eggplant slices in olive oil until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to serving platter; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining eggplant slices.
Remove to serving platter and sprinkle with tomato.
Cover with aluminum foil; let stand 2 minutes or until tomato is heated through.
Serves 4.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Cook until potatoes are done.
Roll out dough according to directions from Bisquick box.
Mix and add thin strips to potato mixture.
Boil gently a minute or two and turn off heat.
Place a lid on the pot and let steam for a few minutes.
Use a larger pot (about a 4-quart size one).
Serve with Cheddar cheese and goldfish crackers.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Mix oleo, powdered sugar and milk.
Divide and flavor as you choose.
Chill.
Roll into balls and chill overnight.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chips and milk together; add nuts, vanilla and salt. Pour into dish and let cool.
When firm, cut in squares.
(Peanut butter or butterscotch chips can also be used in place of chocolate.)

title: watergate fruit salad
directions: Combine pudding mix with pineapple, including juice.
Fold in Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.
Chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter and oil together.
Sift together salt, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Cool in refrigerator.
Roll in balls and flatten with a glass bottom moistened and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Unwrap Reese's cups and set aside.
Line miniature muffin tins with paper liners.
Slice cookies into 10 equal slices, then cut the slices into quarters.
Place 1 quarter into each paper liner. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffy and light brown. Remove from oven and immediately put 1 Reese's cup in center of each cookie.
Makes 40 cups.
Great at Christmastime!

title: giblet gravy
directions: Boil giblets and neck until done; dice.
Add enough water to drippings to give you a fair amount of gravy base.
Bring to boil. Mix flour well with water to make a paste.
Add to drippings to thicken.
Add giblets and neck meat.
Add eggs and salt and pepper to taste and simmer.

title: grilled london broil
directions: Sprinkle garlic salt lightly on both sides of steak.
Prick both sides of steak with fork.
Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oil; pour over steak.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours at room temperature, turning frequently.
Remove steak from marinade. Cook over medium coals about 15 to 20 minutes on each side for medium.
Baste while cooking with marinade.
Slice very thin on a diagonal.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine vanilla pudding, lemon jello and 2 c. water; bring to a boil.
Stir in lemon juice.
Partially set.
Mix strawberry jello with boiling water; chill.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Mix dream whip and add nutmeg.
Fold into pudding mixture; chill. Pour half of pudding mixture into dish.
Pour cranberry mixture over the top.
Cover with remaining half of pudding mixture.
Set. Note: Double recipe makes full 9 X 13 dish.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 3 minutes.
After boiling, add salt, oatmeal and nuts.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow time for cookies to harden.

title: maple cream balls
directions: Boil syrup and salt to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Add butter.
Add flavoring. Beat until creamy.
Add 1/2 the nuts.
Continue beating until mixture is sufficiently firm to mold into small balls.
Roll balls in remainder of nuts.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Watch so it doesn't burn. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and salt.
Blend well. Add chocolate and shortening; blend.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Frost, when cooled.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on sliced muffins.
Bake at 350°.
Cut in wedges and serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar.	Add eggs and milk.
Add rind of	1
lemon
and nuts.
Cream again.
Add flour, baking powder and
salt;	cream.	Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: sour cream green enchiladas
directions: Saute the onions in oil.
Add chilies, tomatoes and salsa. Cook 15 minutes. Add the milk. Cook 15 minutes more. Add sour cream; mix and heat.
Fry tortillas (15 to 30 seconds each) and place in sauce for a short time.
Lift out onto a plate and sprinkle with yellow cheese.
Usually 3 to a stack for each serving.
(I usually make this in a casserole rather than fixing each serving separately.) Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: harley and quinn's baked french toast
directions: Using a 11 x 13 inch lightly oiled pan, line the bottom with 1/2 of the bread cubes.
Next, layer the cream cheese on top of the bread.
Then add the remaining bread cubes on top.
Beat the eggs, maple syrup, milk, and cinnamon together.
Pour entire mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut yellow or zucchini squash in chunks into a 2-quart casserole.
Add sour cream, chicken soup and cheese.
Mix frosted flakes or corn flakes crumbs with butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven until squash is tender.

title: calico chicken
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken, onion, garlic and thyme in oil until chicken is done.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: buck horn inn's broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients together until mixture is blended.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: potatoes in wine and cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange potatoes in greased casserole dish. Melt butter and saute onion.
Spoon over potatoes.

title: mom's chicken croquettes
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion.
Cook until soft and browned.
Add flour and stir.
Slowly add stock; stir, over low heat, until thick.
Season to taste.
Add chicken and chill.
Shape into croquettes.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs; fry in deep hot fat.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients except raisins and nuts.
After mixing well add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Very good, like spice cake.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, saving 2 tablespoons beet liquid.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add vinegar and beet liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Add beets and 1 tablespoon butter.
Heat.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: hot tuna pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard, sugar, basil and salt.
Stir in shells, tuna and veggies.
Serve hot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: key lime filling(pie)
directions: Place all ingredients, except the lime slices and mint leaves, into a blender container or small bowl.
Cover and blend or beat until well mixed.
Pour the filling into hard meringues, baked pie crust or tart crust.
Garnish with lime slices and mint leaves, if desired.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; brown and set aside. Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender. Force Italian plum tomatoes through strainer.
Add tomato liquid, parsley, basil, rosemary, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper to skillet.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms and olives.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes or until sauce is desired consistency.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat vinegar and egg in a measuring cup; fill cup with milk.
Mix with dry ingredients. Roll out into 5 single crusts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl (except cheese).
Pour into a lightly
greased baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; add cheese over top and bake another 10 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate pie
directions: Mix eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until boils and pour into baked pie shell and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar; blend in egg and vanilla flavoring. Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crab cakes, casserole or dip
directions: Make white sauce using butter, flour and milk.
Let cool.
Add egg, mayonnaise, salt, pepper to taste, chives, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and cayenne pepper.
Add crumbs; fold in crab meat carefully.
Make cakes and brown in shortening.
If put in casserole, make white sauce thinner or double number of cracker crumbs.
Bake casserole 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Dip made same as casserole.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add onion and celery and cook briefly.
Mix with dry ingredients and turkey broth.
Stuff turkey loosely or bake separately.
Bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: one serving cheese puff
directions: Cut bread into strips, place with buttered side down along the sides and on the bottom of 10-ounce custard cups.
In a bowl, lightly beat the egg; add milk, cheese, onion salt, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Pour into custard cup.
Place on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until puffy and golden brown. Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.
Let set overnight, then serve.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash
cabbage
and
cut
into 4 wedges (do not separate leaves).
Cook
bacon in a Dutch oven until crisp;
remove and drain
bacon.
Reserve
3 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven. Crumble
bacon.
Combine
cabbage, bacon, red pepper, salt and water
in
Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add
corned
beef and cook an additional 10 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: spanish rice i
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan, add chili powder, garlic powder, salt and rice; mix well.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low.
Do Not Lift the Lid for 30 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl adding 7 up last.
Add drops of red food coloring as desired (optional)
Stir.
Float blocks of ice or add ice cubes.
Add orange and lemon slices.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper.
Drain off any fat that accumulates.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Drain kidney beans, reserving liquid.
Add kidney beans to meat mixture. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes more.
6 servings.

title: cheese pit
directions: Alternate layers of bread and cheese in a greased casserole dish.
Mix milk, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire and add to eggs.
Mix well and pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand several hours or overnight (can stand 2 nights in refrigerator).

title: pumpkin raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add pumpkin and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: christmas cookies(this came out of a 1936 asheville times newspaper)
directions: Blend the shortening and sugar; then add the well-beaten egg and the coconut.
Mix and sift the flour and baking powder and add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.
Beat well together.
Bake in a shallow greased pan in moderate oven (300°) for 30 minutes.
Cut in finger lengths and roll in coconut.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken (the part that has 2 bones); cut slightly at both ends and peel bone out.
Mix ingredients and marinate chicken overnight.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except walnuts.
Bake in small casserole for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Serve with crackers.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together but powdered sugar.
Dough will be soft.
Using a teaspoon, drop onto powdered sugar to coat lightly on each side and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown (do not overcook; cookies should be soft when you take them up).
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Cover dough; let rise until doubled.
Flatten dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with raisins, citron and spices.
Roll up; divide in 12 equal pieces.
Shape each in a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Cover loosely; let rise until doubled.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Form cross on each with icing.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening, then add warm water.
Will make approximately 24 crusts.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and slice enough sweet potatoes to fill 1 ready-to-bake pie shell.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over cooked, sliced potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Roll into balls and then into sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: Cut each hot dog into thirds.
Cut bacon strips into thirds or long enough to go around the hot dog.
Secure with a toothpick and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top and bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until sugar melts and bacon is cooked.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: Cook frozen broccoli. Arrange in a baking pan. Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and grated Parmesan cheese. Have a 5 pound turkey or chicken cooked and slice it up. Arrange over broccoli. Melt 6 ounces butter. Add 3 ounces of flour to butter and salt to taste after adding 1 1/2 quarts of milk, stirring constantly until thickened. Add 1 1/2 cups slightly beaten egg yolks. Stir until blended. Pour over turkey and broccoli. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: cranberry stuffing balls
directions: Cut cranberries in half.
Cook sausage, celery and onion until sausage is done and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients and enough broth to hold mixture together.
Shape into 8 to 10 balls.
Place in a greased, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: italian veggie chicken (microwave)
directions: Cut chicken into large bite size pieces and place in plastic bag with 1 tablespoon honey and 2/3 cup Italian dressing. Refrigerate overnite.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar in lightly greased casserole.
In a separate bowl, combine brown sugar and flour. Cut in butter until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Sprinkle mixture over cranberries.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: easy southern peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Slice peaches into glass baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter slices.

title: christmas date ball
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Turn into an ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and while hot beat with wooden spoon.
When cool, form into small ball and roll in granulated sugar.
Very good.

title: rice and green chile casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine chilies and sour cream. Layer rice, cheese and sour cream mixture.
Start and end with rice.
Top with Cheddar cheese and cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend sausage, bread crumbs, egg and lemon juice.
Form into balls.
Cook in heavy skillet until cooked thoroughly, turning often.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 well beaten eggs, one at a time.
Sift and add flour 1 cup at a time.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: raspberry swirl
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press into well-greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Beat yolks in bowl at high speed until thick.
Add cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth and light.
Beat whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold whites and whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Puree raspberries in mixer or blender.
Gently swirl half through the cheese filling.
Spread mixture in crust.
Spoon remaining puree onto top and swirl with knife.
Freeze, then cover and return to freezer.
Remove just about 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Turn into a crust-lined pan and bake.
Use a rather high temperature at first, to cook the bottom and sides of crust.
Reduce the temperature and continue cooking until a silver knife inserted in center, comes out clean. Do not let the pie boil, as that will make it watery.

title: cari's dragon chili(this is a quick, delicious chili for a cold winter night.)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot or heavy saucepan.
Simmer 45 minutes. Serve topped with mashed potatoes or grated cheese.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add
eggs
and vanilla.
Sift soda, flour and
baking powder; mix into butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Pour 1/2 of batter
in	pan, in a separate bowl mix additional sugar, nuts and cinnamon.	Sprinkle
of cinnamon mixture over batter in
the pan.
Pour
remaining
batter
in pan and sprinkle remaining topping
on
cake.	Bake
at
350°	for
35 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fry bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Add shortening to dry ingredients and blend.
Add water and mix.
Knead dough until it begins to pull away from your hands.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef in large pot; drain.
Then rinse and drain in water (this reduces fat).
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.
This serves approximately six people.

title: cowless cow patties
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and soda, mixing well.
Add coconut, nuts, corn flakes and chocolate chips.
Mix and drop by large spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Spread each one slightly with back of spoon.
Bake 15 minutes or more in a 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer tortillas, chicken and soup mixture to which you have added soup, chicken broth, onion, green chilies and grated cheese on top of each layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 1 hour and reheat.

title: black dragon dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Mix all soups and wine together in large baking dish.
Add meat.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Can use more raisins and nuts.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans into casserole.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Makes a very large bowl.

title: play doh
directions: Bring water, salt and food coloring to a boil. Remove from heat and add alum, oil and flour.
Knead.
Store in plastic bag. No need to refrigerate.

title: blender bread
directions: Measure 2 cups flour in bowl; set aside.
In blender, add the warm water, 1 cup flour and the yeast; blend for 20 seconds.
Add the oil, sugar, salt and egg; blend 20 seconds.
Pour mixture over flour; stir with fork.
Let rise until double.
Shape rolls; let rise again.
Bake in greased pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: brownies kay weatherly
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add margarine and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan, grease and flour well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (will be very chewy and moist).

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces and cook according to directions; drain and cool.
Beat egg in a large bowl.
Add milk, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, salt and garlic salt.
Stir in cooked spaghetti, mix well.
Spread mixture in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan with sides to prevent sauce from running over.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
