Spread tomatoes over spaghetti, sprinkle with oregano, basil and remaining 3 cups cheese.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper, ripe olives and sausage or pepperoni.

title: philly dip
directions: Cover bottom of large pot or wok with oil.
Add a 1-inch square of margarine.
Melt.
Add enough popcorn to be covered by margarine and salt.
Cover and pop and eat.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and graham crackers; press in bottom of pan.
Cook milk and marshmallows; let cool.
Whip cream, then add pineapple.
When milk and marshmallows are cool, mix with cream. Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter and margarine in a saucepan.
Add other ingredients, except shrimp.
Place shrimp in a baking pan and pour heated sauce over, coating well.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn shrimp and cook another 10 minutes. Use leftover sauce for dipping.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add brown sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pineapple over sugar mixture.
Beat egg yolks.
Add granulated sugar and pineapple juice; mix well.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold flour mixture into egg whites.
Pour over fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix - shape in small bowl lined with saran or handiwrap. Chill then roll in nuts and parsley - Refrigerate until use.

title: party ham mixture
directions: Combine ham, bacon, cheese and onions in a large mixing bowl. In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add this to ham mixture.
Mix well.
Pour all into well-greased and floured 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes to brown.
Remove from oven and let cool in pan at least 1 hour.
Very good for parties.

title: camper's stew
directions: Brown hamburg or turkey.
Drain all grease.
Add soup and simmer 1/2 hour, stirring once in awhile.
Mash potatoes and top with stew.
Great with homemade cornbread or biscuits.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Saute potatoes in butter until tender and brown.
Add onion and parsley; continue cooking until onion is transparent.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with your hands until you can handle without it sticking. Form into small balls and lay on wax paper. Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips. When melted, dip balls in chocolate and lay on wax paper.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Separate mushroom caps and stems; slice caps thin.
Finely chop stems.
In 3-quart sauce pot melt the oleo.
Add mushrooms and stirring often, cook over brisk heat so mushrooms don't exude their juice.
Over low heat, stir in flour and onion soup mix; stir in boiling water, 2 cups at a time, keeping smooth.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add milk, half and half, salt and pepper.
Reheat. Makes 2 quarts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix one stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Then press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, remaining margarine and sugar for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread mixture over cracker crumbs and put sliced bananas on top.
Spread pineapple over bananas and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and arrange cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, sour cream, eggs and flour.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Grease and lightly flour a tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mushroom squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread.
Cut into squares and toast in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bowl, then stir rest of the ingredients in. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until rice has absorbed all liquid.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat off.
Add hot taco sauce, garlic salt, cream of mushroom soup, chicken with rice soup, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Crumble 1/2 tortillas in bottom of pan.
Put layer of meat mixture then another layer of tortillas then layer of meat.
Top with shredded cheese (whatever cheese you prefer).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: moist gingerbread(microwave)
directions: Stir the dry ingredients together.
Using a mixer on medium speed, blend in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased microwave-safe tube pan.
Microwave on Medium-high for 6 minutes. Allow to cool in the pan before slicing and serving.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Mix Bisquick, Italian seasoning, pepper and garlic powder. Coat chicken in this mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove chicken from oven.
Spoon pizza sauce over chicken and cover with cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: hot cranberries and apples
directions: Put washed, drained berries into 9x13-inch pyrex dish.
Add apples.
Sprinkle sugar over top.

title: chilled fruit toss
directions: Drain lychees, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Halve lychees. Combine reserved liquid, orange marmalade and ginger root in serving bowl.
Combine lychees, loquats, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Drizzle orange marmalade mixture over fruit.
Stir gently.
Chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve in individual dishes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Melt oleo; add dates and sugar.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add rice cereal, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 60.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make golden brown roux of oil and flour.
Add onion, green pepper and celery and cook slowly until clear.
Add tomato sauce and cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp (if raw, cook until pink), salt and black and red pepper.
Add water, if necessary.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, stir in parsley and onion tops.
Serve on rice.
Serves 8.

title: red satin punch
directions: Combine fruit juices in punch bowl.
Add ice.
Pour in chilled 7-Up slowly.
Ice may be colored to match punch by adding a few drops of food coloring to water before freezing.
Yields 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Mix pineapple and whipped topping.
Fold in the apples, candy and peanuts.
Chill covered until serving time.

title: plucking cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put down in pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: creamed cucumbers and onions
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and milk together in a blender. Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let sit a day or two.

title: mean salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate 8 hours prior to use.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Next add the browned and drained ground beef.
Spoon Ranch Style beans on top of beef. Mix together the chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer this on top of the Ranch Style beans.
Cover with the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate 24 hours, turning bowl upside down.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put in greased pan all ingredients and top with 2 cups rolled corn flakes and 1/4 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab meat treat
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on Pepperidge Farm party bread or toasted bread.

title: party popcorn
directions: In large bowl, place popcorn.
In 1-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat (2 to 3 minutes).
Follow directions for desired variation.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter kiss
directions: Set aside first 3 ingredients.
Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add Kiss and press.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes.

title: lillian calls boiled cake
directions: Boil the first 8 ingredients until raisins are soft.
Cool and add the next 3 ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for an hour or until done.

title: banana, blueberry, walnut muffins
directions: Using food processor:
Mash bananas.
Add eggs and blend.
Add dry ingredients, blend.
Add the walnuts and pulse once or twice. Add blueberries and fold in by hand.
Do not process.
Put in nonstick muffin tin, 1/2 full and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Muffins freeze well, too!

title: oriental braised chicken
directions: *In the oriental section of your market.

title: j&k's crazy queso
directions: Dice cheese into 1-inch squares. Put into large bowl. Melt in microwave for 2 minutes and stir. Continue until melted. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and heat for 2 more minutes. Stir well. Serve with tortilla chips. Enjoy!

title: goose crockettes, pomeranian style
directions: Mix goose meat with onions, garlic, salt, pepper, thyme, marjoram, eggs and flour.
Prepare a good meat dough.
Tasteful.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat 15 minutes. Spread out in pie shell.
Next, layer sliced bananas, then crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over this; sprinkle with pecans and diced cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown sausage and cut into slices.
Cook the noodles.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; combine with all ingredients.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: You will need a large bowl.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in hot greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: orange whipped cream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Make a custard from orange juice and rind, lemon juice and rind, sugar and eggs.
Cook until gets to custard stage; cool.
Whip heavy cream and fold orange mixture into it.
Put filling between layers of cake and spread over entire cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry sponge cake
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole dish.
Grease sides and bottom. In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla. Add melted oleo.
Stir well and pour back into greased casserole. Batter will be thin.
Spoon cherries on top.
Do not stir in.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet pepper shish kabobs
directions: Cut peppers into 2-inch pieces.
Thread pepper pieces and mushrooms on 4 (6-inch) skewers.
Brush with dressing.
Cook over medium coals for about 6 minutes, basting with more dressing and turning after 3 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: reunion macaroni salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large dutch oven pan add first 7 ingredients.
Warm on medium/low heat.
Cook spaghetti, a little under cooked is good. Add spaghetti to mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13 pan, lightly greased. Sprinkle top with parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: lemon pecan pie (cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, flavoring, nuts and fruit.
Mix well.
Line tube pan with heavy paper.
Grease paper.
Pour batter in pan and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250° or until done.

title: orange baked chicken breasts(makes 5 portions)
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan, meat side up.
Sprinkle onion, rosemary, paprika and pepper over chicken.
Blend flour with orange juice and pour over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for 60 minutes, uncovered, until done, basting often with juice.

title: meat nachos
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Dice half of onion to add to meat.
Mix in chili powder and hot sauce.
Salt and pepper for taste.
Place chips on a plate.
Sprinkle meat over chips; add cheese, tomatoes, onion and lettuce.

title: jamaican rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine milk, egg yolks, salt and sugar in a 2-quart saucepan; stir well to blend.
Add rice, vanilla and nutmeg.
Bring to slow boil over low heat, stirring constantly. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in raisins and rum and remove from heat. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with butter.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over bottom of pan and spoon rice mixture atop bread crumbs.
Sprinkle pineapple atop pudding.
Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sleeping angel cookies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Add salt to egg whites; beat to soft peak. Add sugar and whip until stiff.
Add chips and nuts; fold in with spoon.
Drop by spoonful onto aluminum foil-lined cookie sheet. Place in oven. Turn oven off.
Don't peek (they are sleeping). Leave overnight.

title: metairie country club potatoes
directions: Mix bacon with bacon grease, mushrooms and shallots.
Mix in 1/2 cup flour (off the heat).
Add salt, pepper and margarine. Add chopped potatoes.
Mix well with all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glaze for ribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving-sized pieces.
Put ribs in a roasting pan.
combine soy sauce, pepper and Tabasco sauce and spread over meat.
Pour on the honey.
Let stand for 1/2 hour. Turn spareribs over
and
baste
with
sauce.
Let
stand
for another 1/2 hour.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cook roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder until tender. Reserve liquid that roast cooked in.
(I use a pressure cooker for meat.)
When meat is cool, shred into small stringy pieces.
Add all ingredients and meat to meat juices.
Cook until very little juice is left and onion is tender.
Place a small amount of meat mixture in center of tortilla.
Roll, folding both ends in.
Fry in 1 1/2 inches Crisco until golden brown.
Sprinkle with cheese while still hot.
Serve with favorite chili sauce.

title: chess pies
directions: Make a rich pastry and line muffin tins (12 medium).

title: taglarins
directions: Mix noodles, corn, tamales and ripe olives together.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Sprinkle with aged Cheddar cheese and butter.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creole lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until white. Add eggs and cream.
Blend.
Add flour, baking powder and lemon juice, in that order.
Blend.
Bake 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put layer of Tater Tots, then a layer of sliced onions.
Continue until all Tater Tots and onions are used.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over layers of Tater Tots and onions.
Then pour one-half can of beef bouillon soup over the mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heat
oven
Grease
a 13 x 9-inch pan or use Pam. Sprinkle
coconut
and
nuts
evenly over bottom of pan. Mix
the cream cheese, melted butter and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy and set aside.
Mix your cake mix and spread over coconut and nuts.
Spread cream cheese mixture (use spoon to
kind	of drop) over the cake within 1 inch of the sides of the edge of pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until a toothpick
comes out clean in the cake.	Leave in pan and cool completely.
Cut in squares and invert on the plate.

title: banana split
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, oleo and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish on sides and bottom.
Slice bananas and place them evenly.
Drain pineapple and spread for next layer.
Mix cream cheese, milk and confectioners sugar.
Blend until smooth. Pour over last layer.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Place cherries on Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a soft boil.
Set in cold water, add butter and vanilla.
Let it get a little hard.
Then mix with the mixer until it becomes stiff.
Add nuts and pour into a buttered platter.

title: tomato swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle beef
with
the
flour, salt and pepper.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; add onion and celery.
Cook for 2 minutes,
stirring.
With a slotted spoon, remove to a bowl. Add beef
to
the
skillet;
brown well on both sides.	Return onion and
celery to the skillet.
Stir in the stewed tomatoes and Worcestershire
sauce.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2
hours,
or
until
the
beef is fork-tender after stirring often
and	adding	water, if necessary, for a sauce. Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired, before serving.

title: loaf bread
directions: Heat milk and shortening over low heat until warm.
Mix 2 cups of flour with sugar, yeast and salt.
Stir milk mixture into that, then add 2 more cups of flour until it makes soft dough and leaves sides of bowl.
Pour dough on floured surface and knead the other 1 1/2 cups of flour in.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl at once and cover and let rise to double its size, then press dough down to get all air bubbles out.
Divide in 1/2 and put in 2 greased loaf pans and let rise to double its size.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: black walnut and honey ice cream
directions: In saucepan blend milk and honey.
Cook and stir until hot (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir moderate amount of hot mixture into beaten eggs; return to saucepan.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Cool to room temperature.
Balen in whipped cream and vanilla.
Stir in black walnuts.
Freeze mixture in ice cream freezer, according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Combine first five ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Prepare stuffing according to box instructions.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 portions.

title: pork chops dogwood
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Arrange sweet potatoes, pineapple, prunes and cherries on each.
Add pineapple juice; turn on low and steam for 45 minutes.

title: indoor smores
directions: Melt 5 cups marshmallows, chocolate chips and butter in a 3 qt. pan over low heat. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Butter a 13 x 9 pan. Pour cereal in a big bowl. Pour marshmallow mixture over cereal. Stir until coated then add other cup of marshmallows. Press into pan with buttered back of spoon.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans well and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken wings
directions: Heat soy sauce, margarine, brown sugar, water and mustard until sugar and butter are melted.
Cool slightly.
Pour over chicken wings. Marinate 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain juice.

title: caramel apple strudel
directions: Arrange apple slices in dish.
Stir together caramel topping, water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Cook in microwave oven at high speed for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serves four.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Stir together Pet milk, vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, pepper and mayonnaise.
Chill until ready to serve.
Combine cabbage, carrot and celery.
Chill.

title: velvety chocolate cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Combine butter, water and cocoa in a saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well; cool.
Add eggs and buttermilk mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening. Add eggs and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in by hand the nuts and cherries. Form into rolls and wrap in wax paper. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Slice and sprinkle with granulated sugar. Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 8 minutes on bottom shelf and 2 minutes on top shelf.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Save broth.
Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add can of broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fay's pie crust
directions: Mix all the first 3 ingredients together. Blending well, add enough ice water to stick dough together, then roll 9-inch pie crust.

title: party punch
directions: Add the sherbet and ginger ale just before you are ready to serve.
Makes 2 punch bowls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, sugar and oil; beat until foamy. Stir in the zucchini.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt, then add nuts and mix.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Freeze and slice as needed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Add celery and onions.
Barely cover with water; cook until tender.
Drain well in colander.
Put in bowl.
Add well beaten egg, melted butter, cheese and bread that has been cut in small pieces.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup cheese; dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Test by inserting knife.
Serves 8.

title: best-ever corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together. Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 10.

title: oatmeal meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, milk, ground meats and seasonings.
Add oatmeal. Shape in loaf.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Pour tomato puree over top and garnish with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat for 10 minutes the first 4 items.
Cool and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts. Make into small balls.
On wax paper, place either coconut or powdered sugar and roll balls.
Some ladies prefer the sugar, others prefer the coconut.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, shake, and store in an airtight container.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sprinkle 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon over apples and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs, cooking oil, vanilla and orange juice, then add baking powder, baking soda and walnuts.
Mix all by hand.
Batter is too thick for electric beater.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Alternate batter and apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Mix together crushed graham crackers and melted butter.
Layer in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the chips, nuts and coconut in pan.
Pour 1 can condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool, cut in squares and serve.

title: ham jambalaya style
directions: Saute green pepper, celery, onion and garlic in hot oil in 10-inch skillet until tender (do not brown). Add tomato sauce and chili powder. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Stir in ham, tomato juice and Tabasco sauce. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Serve over rice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef and carrots over rice
directions: Trim fat and cube roast.
Pour tomato juice in large baking dish.
Stir in tapioca.
Add meat, carrots, celery and onion. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Place apples in shallow baking dish, 6 x 10-inch. Sprinkle with mixture of water, cinnamon and salt. Work together until crumbly the sugar, flour and butter. Spread crumb mixture over apples. Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes. Serve warm with plain or whipped cream. Serves 6.

title: date nut roll
directions: Put 1/2 of crackers crumbs in a large bowl; add nuts, marshmallows and dates.
Add enough milk to mix good.
Add the rest of milk and most of crumbs.
Save enough crumbs to roll dough in.
Shape into rolls and wrap in tinfoil.
Keep in refrigerator 1 week before cutting.

title: momma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dump into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips in a bowl.
Mix with spoon until moistened.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab supremes
directions: Pick over crabmeat and remove any cartilage.
Place in 1-quart bowl and flake with a fork.
Add celery, mustard, pickle relish, green onions and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook water, sugar and corn syrup until it spins a thread (230° to 234°).
Add peanuts and cook until they begin to pop (hard crack stage 300° to 310°).
Add soda, butter and salt.
Pour onto a large greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: christmas or hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add beaten eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened, but do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans or well-oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes in cake pans or bake at 325° for 1 hour in tube pan.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: swiss-rosti
directions: Coarsely grate the potatoes into a dish of cold water.
Brown butter lightly in a large heavy pan.
Blot potatoes on a towel to dry them.
Add to hot butter and press firmly with a broad spatula.
Reduce heat and sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered for about 15 to 20 minutes, until bottom of potatoes are cooked and golden brown.
Turn into a hot serving plate, crusty side up.
Serve immediately.

title: presbyterian chicken
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with chipped beef.
Wrap 1/2 piece of bacon around each breast.
Place in casserole.
Cover with soup and sour cream which have been mixed together.
Bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
You might want to cover with aluminum foil for part of the time.

title: russian dill pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water, pickling spices, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Put cucumbers in cold water for 2 hours, then slice in jars.
Do not peel.
Put sprig of dill in each, along with a slice of red and green pepper.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Pour boiling mixture over cucumbers.
Seal and set jars in boiling water and let cool.

title: mom's home made buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in luke warm water.
Add 1 1/2 c. flour. Beat until smooth.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Melt butter.
Line pie shells with cheese and bacon.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Stir in cream and butter. Then pour mixture over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature of oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes more, until quiche is bubbly and golden brown.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugars, egg and vanilla together in bowl until creamy.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in coconut and cornflakes.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool slightly, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients.
Turn into shallow buttered baking dish.
Spread on the topping.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: red cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in frypan. Add other ingredients.
Steam in frypan for 1 1/2 hours, covered, on low heat. Add water, if necessary.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease (adding onions if desired). Add soup without water.
Add tomato sauce and simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze brim.
Add carrot and green pepper.
Boil together vinegar, sugar and celery seed for 1 minute.
Cool completely.
Mix cabbage mixture together with vinegar mixture.
Can be frozen over and over and over again.

title: chop suey
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Add pork and cook until vegetable are done.
Add soy sauce, sugar, bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Thicken mixture with flour dissolved in water.
Serve over rice.

title: corn dogs(microwave)
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, onion, baking powder, salt and mustard.
Stir in egg, corn, milk and hot pepper sauce.
Spoon batter into greased round baking dish with inverted glass in center.
Place hot dogs around dish in spoke-like fashion.
Heat 13 1/2 to 14 1/2 minutes on Power level 5 (Medium), until cornbread is done.
Remove glass and let stand, covered, 7 minutes before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread on plate or pan 14 inches in diameter.

title: corn casserole
directions: Warm rice.
Cook and drain corn.
Drain pimento.
Saute onion, oleo, bell pepper, salt and pepper.

title: hot carrots(good to add to salad.)
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add jalapenos and juice, onions, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Chill at least 3 hours. Flavor peaks when thoroughly chilled.
Jalapenos can be adjusted according to hotness desired.

title: dutch puff(kids love this)
directions: Mix flour, milk and eggs all together with hand mixer.
Place 1/2 stick margarine in jelly roll pan (cookie sheet pan with sides.)
Melt in oven at 425°.
Spread it all over pan.
When oleo bubbles, pour in flour, milk and egg mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
The mixture puffs up, making hills and valleys and hanging over the sides of the pan.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour the milk into a large bowl.
Add the pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let the pudding mixture stand for 5 minutes. Stir in the Cool Whip topping and half of the crushed cookies. Set out 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of crushed cookies into each cup.
Then fill each cup about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with the remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Decorate with worms and flowers to make your cups look like dirt!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and warm the 1 cup of juice.
Dissolve jello and sugar in juice, then add juice of 1 lemon.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Whip jello mixture; whip chilled evaporated milk.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Add fruit cocktail and all other fruits.
Put crushed graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch dripper pan.
Pour in the mixture.
Top with more cracker crumbs. Set in fridge all day or until set well.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: classic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs; gradually add flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 9 1/2 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
4 1/2 dozen.

title: rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water to sugar and Crisco.
Set aside and add yeast cake in 1/4 cup water to dissolve.
Add this to 1 well beaten egg.
Add flour to mixture a little at a time.
Be sure to beat until smooth after each addition.
This makes for lighter rolls.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.
Put rolls out about 2 hours before baking time.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: fresno lamb shanks
directions: Place lamb shanks in roaster.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover roaster and
cook 3 hours in a slow 300° oven.
If shanks are large, raise temperature to 325° or 350°.
Remove cover. Continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Cut peaches in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and cool in refrigerator.

title: french toast
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs; then stir in wheat germ, water, vanilla and sugar.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Dip each bread slice into egg mixture.
Place in frying pan and cook until bread is brown on both sides.
Serve with butter or syrup.

title: camp stew
directions: Brown ground beef in hot fat.
Add onion and saute until clear.
Add next 7 ingredients and bring to boil.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add rice and cook another 10 minutes.
Best served with corn bread.

title: spinach dumplings
directions: Thaw the spinach and squeeze dry; add the 2 eggs, Ricotta cheese, bread crumbs, grated cheese, chopped onions, garlic salt, basil and flour.
Mix well.
You may need to add more flour if too soft.
Shape into balls about the size of meatballs.
Roll in flour.
Bring water to a boil.
Cook small amount at a time.
They will sink to bottom.
When cooked they will rise to the top, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Keep warm.
When they are all cooked, top with your favorite tomato sauce and cheese.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and chill.
Beat the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Add half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust; arrange half of strawberries.
Prepare pudding with milk; pour over strawberries and chill.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding; garnish with remaining strawberries.

title: lemon honey chicken
directions: Dredge chicken cutlets in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour 1/4 of that melted butter over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "frog eye" salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Save juice; measure 1 3/4 cup juice.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly (can put in refrigerator).
This must be cold before adding pudding.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then add 1 cup of the Cool Whip. Blend.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding mix and milk. Beat.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread the remainder of the Cool Whip on top.
Can put nuts on top if desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Stir together and pat into a buttered 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Mix oleo in 9x13-inch baking dish. Mix first 4 ingredients for batter, pour over oleo. Mix cocoa and sugar, sprinkle over batter, pour water slowly over top. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Good served warm, cold or with ice cream.

title: dianne's russian tea
directions: Combine tea, sugar, water and fruit juices.
Simmer to serve. May refrigerate and heat when ready to serve.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve syrup.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup, heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in the mixture. Let cool and slowly stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set, 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce together and mix into the jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: orange chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Preheat a nonstick pan. Brown the chicken pieces in the nonstick pan.
Pour the teriyaki sauce over the chicken. Add the orange slices.
Cover the chicken and cook over low heat for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
(Cook until pieces are tender and sauce is thick.)
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fruity pound cake
directions: Mix and sift first five ingredients.
Stir in almonds.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly but do not beat.
Spoon into well-oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 28 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before turning out of pan.
If you use nuts other than almonds, use the same type extract.

title: pool hall slaw
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 30 minutes; stir regularly.
Makes a gallon.

title: chef salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and reserve oil.
Combine with next 9 ingredients in salad bowl.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss with reserved oil and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti as package directs.
In saucepan, over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 minutes.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Gradually add milk, sherry, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in bowl.
Mix slightly. Put cream cheese and butter in center of mixture.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut and serve.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Shred cheese. Melt margarine in large skillet; add mushroom soup and water.
Mix well; add other ingredients.
Mix; pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook and stir onion, green pepper, garlic and ginger in melted butter in Dutch oven over medium-high heat until onion is soft. Add curry powder; cook 1 minute.
Add broth, water and broccoli. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until broccoli is very tender.
Puree soup, in batches, in blender or food processor until smooth.
Return to Dutch oven.
Stir in enough half and half to give soup desired consistency.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat through. Do not boil.
To serve, ladle into bowls.
Garnish with croutons. (To serve cold, refrigerate, covered, until chilled.)

title: scooby snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shake well with ice and serve in a highball glass.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Alternate cake mix and flour with milk.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in tube pan or until tests done.

title: edible ornaments(easter nests or christmas wreaths)
directions: Place margarine in a medium bowl.
Microwave at High for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows, stirring to coat. Microwave at High 30 to 60 seconds or until marshmallows puff and mixture can be stirred smooth.
Stir in crushed cereal.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Garnish with additional chopped nuts, if desired.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple, water and sugar.
Add jello and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add celery and nuts.	Refrigerate. When slightly jelled fold in Dream Whip and put in mold.
Chill until set.

title: hamburger stroganoff(for the microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes or until meat losses pink color.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream; mix well.
Cover.
Microwave at High 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Blend in sour cream.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Serve over noodles, stirring once. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange breakfast loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine sugars and 1/2 teaspoon orange peel; set aside.

Reserve 1 teaspoon margarine; separate biscuits and brush tops with remaining margarine. Sprinkle tops with the brown sugar mixture, about 1 teaspoon. Arrange biscuits into a loaf by holding 1 biscuit on its side and gently pressing the sugared side against the unsugared side of another biscuit; repeat procedure, using all the biscuits. Carefully transfer loaf to a nonstick loaf pan and brush top with reserved teaspoon margarine.
Bake until loaf is lightly browned, about 35 minutes.
Transfer loaf from pan to wire rack and let cool slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients except parsley and nuts.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into a ball and roll in parsley or nuts.

title: quick peanut blossoms
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, water and egg.
Stir by hand until dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
If necessary, refrigerate dough for a short time for easier handling.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with a Hershey kiss and press down firmly, so cookie cracks around edge.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: fancy short ribs
directions: Coat short ribs
with flour.
Cook in oil until browned on all sides.
Add
cups water and remaining ingredients to meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer each item as listed in a large casserole dish. Spread dressing to completely top salad.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, onion, mushroom soup and sour cream in mixing bowl.
In another bowl, pour melted butter over stuffing mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake until crisp on top at 325°.

title: baked potatoes au gratin
directions: Bake potatoes in skins; mash with butter, milk and sour cream. Add remaining ingredients; place in greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: down the road beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Cut up sausage into small pieces.
Cut up onion and green pepper.
Add to hamburger and sausage mixture.
Add all other ingredients together.
Stir well. Bake in a large baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: totally texas cornbread
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients together.
Add corn, garlic, jalapeno peppers and onion, mixing well.
Stir in cheese.
Lightly grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and spread with half of batter.
Spread ground beef evenly over first layer of batter.
Spread remaining batter over ground beef and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma maggie's homemade tomato soup
directions: In large saucepan, add tomatoes and baking soda.
In medium saucepan, add milk, water, salt and pepper.
Heat both pans to warm.
Slowly pour milk pan into tomato pan.
Continue heating to desired temp.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl and set aside.

title: turkey terrazeti or chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except last two, and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef.
Warm soups together with cheese, margarine and milk.
Add noodles (cooked), ground beef with soups and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a large saucepan; mix well.
Combine milk and egg yolks; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Let cool and pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with 1/4 cup toasted coconut.

title: ratatouille
directions: Dice onions.
Chop garlic.
Heat onions and garlic in a pot with 1 tablespoon oil.
Chop green pepper, zucchini and eggplant. Add green pepper and cover.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and eggplant; cover.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off grease.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Press biscuits into muffin pan.
Spoon mixture into shells (approximately 3/4 full).
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Remove from muffin pan.

title: party mix(microwave)
directions: In a large bowl, melt margarine on High for 1 minute. Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.

title: olive-onion pie
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Cook onions slowly in butter in covered pan for 5 to 10 minutes until transparent.
Beat eggs; add sour cream, salt and pepper and beat again.
Stir in onions and olives and turn into pastry-lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (350°) for about 25 to 30 minutes longer or until set in center. Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave fudge brownies
directions: In 8-inch square dish, place butter and cocoa.
Microwave on High 2 minutes; until butter is melted.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Add sugar, flour and butter-cocoa mixture and beat at medium speed on mixer until blended.
Pour mixture into the square dish.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in top of a double boiler over hot water.
Add eggs and stir; cool until lukewarm.
Fold in pecans, marshmallows and coconut; mix well.
Shape in 4 rolls on aluminum foil, covered with a thin coat of powdered sugar (can also use wax paper instead of foil).
Wrap rolls tightly and keep in refrigerator until ready to slice in cookies 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick.
Store in refrigerator and keep tightly covered.
These will also serve nicely as a candy.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots until just barely tender (do not overcook).
Combine with tomatoes, mushrooms and onion.
Mix together the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Mix together for 24 hours; toss carefully a few times.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pecan honeymoon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend Crisco and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Add 1 cup flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Pat evenly in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool; unroll.

title: turnip au gratin
directions: Cook turnips in boiling salted water to cover just until tender.
Drain and spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Combine butter and flour in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until bubbly.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese, salt and pepper, stirring until cheese melts.
Spoon sauce over cooked turnips.
Combine melted butter with breadcrumbs, tossing well; sprinkle over casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat over medium heat, stirring to crumble.
Drain and spoon meat into an 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine baking mix, milk and eggs, beating until smooth. Pour mixture over beef, sauce and cheese, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no frost chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Add flour, salt and cocoa alternately with dates, water and soda.
Add half of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and rest of chocolate chips on batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage stuffed macaroni shells
directions: Prepare shells according to package.
Preheat oven to 375°. Combine Ricotta and egg. Add Mozzarella, parsley, Parmesan, basil and oregano. Stir in finely chopped sausage.
Combine spaghetti sauce and water in bowl.
Put 3/4 cup sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Fill shells with sausage-cheese mixture and place in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Bake 35 minutes or until shells are heated through and cheese is melted.

title: fourth of july casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until crumbly.
Drain excess fat.
Mix together beans, sauce and brown sugar.
Add to ground beef.
Place in greased medium-size baking dish.
Cover top with biscuits (just touching) in one layer.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° until biscuits are brown and casserole is bubbling.

title: sock it to me pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans with an electric mixer. Fold in pecans.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour.
You may top it with nuts if you desire.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form into a loaf. Bake 1 3/4 hours at 350°.
Use meat thermometer (170°) to be sure of doneness.
Don't overcook.

title: stove top chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken on both sides in butter; pour soup over chicken. Let simmer 30 to 45 minutes, covered.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting.

title: gwen's picante sauce
directions: Pour a little tomato juice in blender with your peppers; chop fine.
Add the rest of the ingredients and blend lightly.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix until well blended. Add eggs and Wesson oil. Mix until thoroughly blended. Add prunes and beat thoroughly. Pour into 9-inch lightly greased tube pan. Bake in a 300° oven 1 hour or until well done. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and place cake on racks to cool completely.

title: bess truman's ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar for considerable time until it is very smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and egg mixture. Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in buttered pie pan in medium oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add egg, vanilla, fruit cocktail and syrup.
Beat well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread brown sugar and nuts on top of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: "fairies fruit balls"
directions: Finely chop prunes, dates, raisins and coconut.
Place in a large mixing bowl and stir well.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup pecans; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll each in remaining chopped pecans.
Store in an airtight container, placing waxed paper between layers.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: whole wheat bread mix
directions: In a large aluminum roasting pan or a very large bowl, combine whole wheat flour, unbleached all-purpose flour, salt and dry milk; stir with wire whip or shake in covered bowl until mixed well.
Press brown sugar through a coarse sieve so that it will mix with the flour mixture or whirl the brown sugar with 1 to 2 cups of the flour mixture in a food processor to distribute the brown sugar.
Stir into flour mixture.
Package in 5 to 6 cup quantities in plastic bags; label with dates.
Will store in refrigerator 10 to 12 weeks or you can freeze this mixture up to 6 months.

title: ham for one
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with foil.
Place ham in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with pineapple.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 1 serving.

title: vegetarian pie
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute chopped onion and mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add to cooked broccoli.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Shape into balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375°.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: "local style" party mix
directions: Melt margarine and combine with oil, corn syrup, sugar and shoyu sauce.
Add Crispix and mix well.
Sprinkle furikake and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well between each.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together, reserving 1/4 cup.
Add the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix together remaining flour and the walnuts; add to batter and mix just until blended.
Beat egg whites.
Pour into 8-inch cake pans or one 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for cake pans or 50 to 60 minutes for loaf pan.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and cut meat into pieces about 1 inch square.
Combine all ingredients in a dutch oven, mixing thoroughly.
Cover tightly and bake in a preheated 250° oven for 5 hours.
Stir once or twice during cooking period.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed chicken rolls
directions: Place chicken breasts between plastic wrap and pound flat. Lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper (and garlic powder, as desired).
Arrange spinach leaves overlapping on chicken, leaving approximately 1/4 to 1/2-inch on 3 sides to seal.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Roll up like egg rolls, tucking in sides to seal chicken.
Tie with string or secure with poultry pins.
Grill or broil, turning 4 times to get each side browned (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Can also saute in lightly oiled pan for 10 to 15 minutes, turning to brown.
Serves 6.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg, drain and add to vegetables.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg, bananas and soda.
Add flour; mix well.
Add walnuts.
Grease and flour bottom of loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This recipe freezes well. Double recipe makes 3 loaves.

title: asparagus linguini
directions: Cook onion and garlic in margarine until onions are soft.
Add asparagus, cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice; cook 1 minute.
Season with pepper.
Remove from heat.
Toss hot pasta, Parmesan and asparagus mixture.
Serve on platter; sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup. Bake remainder in 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread over baked mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved dry mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve cool.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend all the ingredients.

title: chocolate pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cocoa, flour, vanilla and pecans. Refrigerate for about 1 hour for easier handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Pinch off pieces of dough the size of marbles.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: beignets (ben-yay)(french doughnuts)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and milk and mix well.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop tablespoon size pieces into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix well.
Cut 2 lbs. lean beef into thin strips, cutting off all fat.
Put in bowl and add salt mixture.
After 1/2 to 1 hour, stir again.
Lay strips on wire rack as close as possible.
Put in 150 oven overnight.
Leave oven door slightly open for an hour.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten egg whites; mix well and pour into pie baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with Cool Whip and sliced bananas.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put 2 cans of refried beans in a saucepan with a few slices of bacon for seasoning (you may need to add 1/2 to 1 cup of water if beans are too thick).
Cover beans; let simmer.
Dice onion and shred cheese.
In a round pie pan, mix together the tomato sauce and Chili-O mix to taste.
Lay tortillas, one at a time, in above mixture to cover both sides of tortilla.
Place tortilla in a skillet with a small amount of grease and lightly fry tortilla on each side.
Place on a plate until each tortilla has been fried.
(Occasionally, you may need to add more grease to skillet.)

title: lia's walnut burgers
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs to blend.
Stir in crumbs, walnuts, green onions, wheat germ, cottage cheese, parsley, basil, oregano, and paprika.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Vigorously whisk, blending until ingredients are smooth.
Chill before serving. Yields 4 cups.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and butter in double boiler; set aside.
Cream sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add, alternately with Milky Way mixture and buttermilk, to the egg-sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat well.

title: saucy fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 2 Tbsp. cocoa.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla, mix only until smooth. Add pecans.
Pour into 1 quart greased baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and 4 Tbsp cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in dish.
Pour boiling water over top.
Bake 350 about 30 minutes.
Serve warm topped with whipping cream or ice cream.
Serves 9.

title: refrigerator coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, topping, sugar and coconut, saving some coconut.
Refrigerate while baking cake.
When layers are cool, spread tops and side with icing and top with remaining coconut. Place cake in tightly covered cake saver and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: virginian's pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Cream well the butter and brown sugar.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture and mix until it resembles coarse meal.
Put into bottom of well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Partially bake for 10 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into lengthwise slices.
Simmer in margarine.
Add onions, mushrooms, celery, green peppers and beef bouillon cubes. Add water and simmer slowly in covered pan until tender, about 3 hours.
If water boils down, add enough to make gravy.
Mix flour with sour cream and add to steak.
Let come to a boil so gravy is smooth and creamy.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cover 14-inch pizza pan with foil.
Cut dough in 1/8 inch pieces and press in pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, then place on serving platter when cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on crust.
Top with fresh fruit (kiwi, banana, strawberries, mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks, blueberries). Glaze with:

title: blushin' bride biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients together.
Roll out 1-inch thick and cut.
Cover bottom of pan with melted butter. Place biscuits into pan, then add add remaining butter to top of biscuits.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake until blushin' golden brown (about 30 minutes).

title: candy-like cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the next 4 ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Do not mix them too long or they will set up before you can get them dropped.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
In large soup kettle, combine all ingredients.
Pour in water just to cover cabbage.
Mix well. Cook until cabbage is tender, stirring often in the beginning, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Put toothpicks in each one for dipping into chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip each ball into chocolate mixture and put onto waxed paper to cool.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Simmer cinnamon and water together 10 minutes; remove cinnamon.
Add juices.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 14 cups.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add the flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, melted butter and half the cheese.*
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 35 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: artichoke chicken with water chestnuts
directions: Brown chicken in hot vegetable oil in large skillet.
Add carrots. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, artichokes, scallions, water chestnuts, thyme and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine cornmeal, 1/2 cup flour, paprika, salt, garlic salt and pepper, mixing lightly.
Add milk, egg and 2 tablespoons oil; beat with a fork until smooth.
Roll each weiner in all-purpose flour; coat evenly with batter, allowing excess to drain.
Heat 1 inch of salad oil to 375°; fry weiners for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain.
Insert wooden skewers in the end of each weiner, and serve with mustard or catsup, if desired.
Makes 8 corn dogs.

title: gesunheit kuchen (god bless you cake)(nana's recipe)
directions: Beat up egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter, sugar and confectioners sugar.
Add egg yolks and almond and vanilla extracts.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour. Alternate the flour with the milk, ending up with flour.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold into the batter.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
About 15 minutes before stew is done, drop batter in little mounds.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Very good in vegetable stew and chicken stew.

title: mincemeat-cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, stir cranberry sauce, mincemeat and orange juice until heated through.
Serve warm over ice cream. Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Yield:
about 3 1/2 cups.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening until looks like coarse meal.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir yeast mixture and buttermilk into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and roll into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick. Spread evenly with butter.
Fold dough in half and cut into 2-inch squares.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Bring to boil syrup, sugar and butter.
Keep stirring until it boils.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, coconut and vanilla.
Drop scant teaspoon of dough on cookie sheet covered with foil.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes.
Pull foil from sheet and cool about 3 to 4 minutes before removing cookies from foil. They peel right off by working fingers on underside of foil.

title: sally's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Peel and dice.
Remove strings from celery; dice and add to potatoes.
Add all other ingredients and fold in mayonnaise to let stand an hour or so before serving.
Serves 50.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt, over hot (not boiling) water, Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: strawberry-white chocolate dessert
directions: In saucepan combine baking bars and 1/4 cup of the cream. Heat and stir over low heat until bars are melted.
Cool slightly. Stir together coffee and brandy.
Set aside.

title: cool cranberry dessert
directions: Cream together mayonnaise, cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapples and cranberries.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Freeze.

title: fresh pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin, eggs and milk in blender or food processor and puree.
In a large bowl, stir together sugar, salt and spices. Pour into pumpkin and butter and stir to mix.
Divide between pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serve with real whipped cream.

title: crazy salad
directions: Makes a large amount.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Grease two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Line with wax paper. Grease wax paper.
Prepare mix for "cake-like" brownies.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top springs back. Cool.
In large bowl mix milk and pudding mix.
Beat.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In large serving bowl, place 1 layer brownies, pudding and strawberries (in that order).
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.

title: sliced baked potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise, just scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into slices, being carefully not to slice all the way through the potatoes.
Put potatoes on a baking dish and fan them out slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.
(Recipe can be microwaved.)

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes.
Cook until done.
Drain well. Cool.
Add pickles, celery, olives, pepper and onion; mix mayonnaise as desired.
Top with paprika.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Mix butter, marshmallows, coloring and vanilla in frypan.
Heat until a smooth consistency.
Add corn flakes.
Working quickly with buttered fingers, use a tablespoon to remove some mixture; shape into wreaths and put on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with colored sugar decorating sprinkles.
Be careful; mixture will be hot.

title: six course dinner
directions: Slice potatoes very thin.
Slice onions and peppers.
Brown hamburger.
In a baking dish, layer potatoes, meat, onion, rice and peppers and cover with tomato juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese until smooth.
Add Taco seasoning mix. Blend thoroughly.
Spread on plate. Spread sour cream on top of cheeses. Add shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped scallions, chopped black olives, top rest with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine peaches, pears and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry pudding over fruit.
Add strawberries.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Add bananas.
Serve.

title: unbaked graham cracker pie shell
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend with fingers, fork or pastry blender.
Press evenly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate. Refrigerate until ready to fill.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Blend crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in shallow dish.
Dip each chicken piece in butter and then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange in shallow foil-lined pan.
Drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. (Do not turn.)

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending well.
Pour into 2 to 3 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix thoroughly pretzels, margarine and brown sugar.
Spread in oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix together 10x sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled first layer.
Dissolve strawberry jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Cool, then spread over cream cheese layer.
After it congeals, spread other 1/2 carton Cool Whip on top.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt the margarine in a pan and add sugar, egg and milk.
Cook until boiling.
Add coconut, pecans and 1 cup ground graham crackers. Mix together.
Pour over whole crackers in pan.
Top with whole crackers; press down slightly.
Top with icing.
Refrigerate. This is best if made the day before.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and add shortening.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: dump cake
directions: In ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, place pineapple and apples. Sprinkle with cake mix.
Dot with
margarine.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Cover with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: baked macaroni, chicken and cheese
directions: (This can be made up to 2 days ahead of serving.)

title: coke salad
directions: Boil pineapple and cherry juice and pour Jell-O.
Let cool. Add remaining ingredients.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: While potatoes are warm, pour dressing over; chill 2 hours. Add celery and onion.
Chop egg whites; add.
Sieve yolks; reserve some for garnish.
Combine remaining sieved yolk with mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours.
Add cucumber.
Sprinkle reserved yolk over top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Allow to thaw about 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pahari chicken
directions: Joint the chicken.
Chop the ginger and 2 green chillies fine. Slit remaining chillies and fry in melted butter with cardamoms, ginger and garlic.
Add chicken pieces and fry until evenly browned.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve when sherbet has melted.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Let stand overnight in 1 gallon of water mixed with 1 cup salt.
Drain next morning real well.
Mix sugar, vinegar, 1 cup of water and 1 teaspoon each of salt, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
The seed may be put into small cloth bags and that way seed are not in the jars.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it; seal and flute.
Cover edge with 3 inch strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken broccoli supreme
directions: Thaw broccoli slightly and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Space chicken evenly atop broccoli and season with 1/2 Nature's seasoning and bacon.
Microwave on High for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Combine soup and Cheddar cheese and spoon over chicken and broccoli, sprinkle other 1/2 of Nature's seasoning.
Cook for 5 minutes on High.
Sprinkle French fried onions and Parmesan cheese.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: harvest sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; mix well. Beat in sweet potatoes. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Set aside. Dip chicken in Italian dressing.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking pan coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and pudding together. Add other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: merry christmas spice cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cardamon and mace.
Set aside. Combine sugar and oil; beat thoroughly, then add eggs, beating well.
Stir in honey and dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add vanilla and 2 teaspoons water; beat well.
Stir in flour and pecans; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Gently shake a few cookies at a time in
a bag with powdered sugar.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar and egg yolks. Beat. Add water or milk mixed with rind, juice, salt and flour. Mix well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour in unbaked crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat marbled cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Stir together margarine and cocoa until smooth.
In bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then flour.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter into medium bowl.
Beat in cocoa mixture.
Spoon half the vanilla batter into prepared pan, then half the chocolate.
Repeat. With knife, cut through batters to marble.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut in greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top of coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix margarine and cream cheese; mix well and add powdered sugar.
Drop by teaspoon on top of cake mixture.
Cook for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: italian style grilled chicken breasts
directions: Slow cook chicken on open grill.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Baste with Italian dressing often to keep moist.
Serves 4.

title: banana pudding in a hurry
directions: Combine
pudding
mix,	egg
yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat,
stirring
constantly,
until it comes to a full boil. Remove
from heat.	Layer wafers and bananas in a 1 1/2 quart dish.
Pour
pudding
mix
over all.
Beat egg whites at high speed of mixer until frothy.
Add sugar slowly, continuing	to beat
until
stiff	peaks form.
Spread over pudding. Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: washington's eggnog
directions: Mix liquor together first. Separate the egg yolks from whites. Beat yolks, then add sugar and mix well. Add liquor mix, drop by drop, to egg mixture, while slowly beating the eggs (if you do this too fast it will curdle the mixture).

Add milk and cream; continue to slowly mix. Add 1/2 tablespoon nutmeg and cinnamon to the mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture. Let set in cool place for several days. The mixture will be very thick.
When ready to serve, stir mixture and let set for about 5 or 10 minutes.

title: icebox hawaiian pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Fold in small carton Cool Whip.
Pour in cooled, baked pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat; add onion and cook until just tender.
Add seasonings, beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash hot potatoes; add milk and egg.
Drop in mounds over meat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or omit potatoes and use biscuits on top.

title: christmas cutouts(portuguese)
directions: Add sugar and egg; blend together.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together.

Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk. Stir in vanilla. Roll out 1/16-inch thick on pastry cloth. Cut in Christmas designs. Brush with egg white. Decorate. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in salted water until tender; drain.
Add water chestnuts and soup; mix well.
Pour into well greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into lightly greased 9x9 pan. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Put 2 quarts water in pot. Add salt and margarine.
Bring to a boil. Add the spaghetti.
Let cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll beef into small balls.
Put in skillet and brown.
Cook until beef is done. Drain spaghetti and beef.
Spoon beef into spaghetti.
Pour in spaghetti sauce. Add 1/2 can water. Let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: ruth's low-fat salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Cover and keep cold.

title: punch
directions: Fill rest of gallon jar with water.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter the bottom of baking dish.
Layer the apples in dish and sprinkle remaining ingredients over apples.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then take cover off and bake 30 more minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together and put into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour on top of coconut and nuts. In saucepan, melt oleo and cream cheese. Heat until mixture is warm enough to stir in 1 pound box of confectioners sugar. Spoon over top of cake mix. Bake at 350° until done. Do not cut until cooled.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread pieces in bottom of greased 9 X 13 pan (grease with butter). Mix other ingredients together and pour on top of bread. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Serve with cream or top with ice cream.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Mix butter and flour as for pie crust. Work in the sour cream and sugar. Pat dough into 16 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Spread over it a thin layer of raspberry preserves.

title: gooey good butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Spread onto the greased pan. Blend the remaining eggs and other ingredients.
Pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheryl's cheese tickles
directions: Grate the cheese.
Cream the butter and cheese.
Sift flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt together. Add to cheese and butter mixture along with Worcestershire sauce. Knead on board. Form in 1-inch rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Leave in refrigerator overnight. Slice in thin slices.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 325° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch salad dressing mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: pina coladas
directions: Blend all ingredients until slushy.
Serves 3.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix everything except soup and chips.
Spread soup over mixture.
Add chips on top.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil the water, salt and vinegar. Pour over medium cucumbers that have been packed into 1/2-gallon jars along with the following: To each jar, place large bunch of fresh dill weed, 3 cloves of garlic, 2 pods hot pepper and 1/4 teaspoon alum. Pour boiling solution over this and seal immediately. Let stand 6 weeks before opening.

title: lemon bar cookies
directions: Mix all together and pat in pan 10 x 13-inch.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken, cut into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Cook pasta and drain.
Saute mushrooms, butter, garlic salt and parsley.
Add chicken to mushroom mixture and let set to blend flavors.

title: banana pudding
directions: Take 5 egg yolks and put in a large microwave bowl. Save egg whites in a saucer. Stir yolks and add flour and sugar. Mix well. Add a little bit of milk until it is smooth. Then add remaining milk and water and stir. Cook in microwave for 3 minutes. Keep repeating until mixture is thick. Add vanilla. Layer wafers, then bananas, then pudding mixture. End with pudding on top.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce and oregano.
Then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then pour tomato sauce over loaf and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: tropical salsa salad
directions: Cut kiwi and banana into chunks.
Place all ingredients in a food processor very briefly.
This has an interesting, different taste.
Yields 3 servings.
Has 130 calories, fat free.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour juices and water in bottom of a percolator.
Put spices in basket of percolator and perk as you would for coffee.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients (except icing) in order given, adding all dry ingredients a
little at a time.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Grease three 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
A cream cheese and powdered sugar icing tinted yellow gives the look of autumn.

title: microwave party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes or until cereal is hot and crisp.
Stir occasionally.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of the cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Place in 2 qt. casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onion rings and bake for 5 minutes more.
5 to 6 servings.

title: hard candy
directions: Sprinkle 18 x 24-inch strip of heavy foil with powdered sugar. Mix granulated sugar, Karo and water in large saucepan.
