Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310°, or until drops of syrup form hard and brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavored oil and coloring.
Pour onto foil; break in pieces.
Sprinkle with plenty of powdered sugar so it won't stick together.
Store in airtight containers.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cheese.
Add sugar to cream cheese and mix well.
Add flour.
Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture into a graham cracker pie crust.
Top with strawberries.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in carrots.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg and add to carrot mixture.
Stir until blended.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (a toothpick inserted in center should come out clean).
Cool.
If desired, remove from pan after cooling 10 minutes.
Cool completely. Lightly sift powdered sugar evenly over a doily on top of cake; carefully remove doily to have a pretty design.
Makes 9 servings.

title: lasagna crescent roll-ups
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in large skillet in oil until tender. Remove from heat; stir in cubed cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and salt.
In small saucepan, heat sauce.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles.
Overlap long sides of 2 rectangles 1/2-inch.
Firmly press edges together.
Roll to form 11 x 6-inch rectangle.
Repeat with remaining rectangles.
Spoon 3/4 cup cream cheese mixture onto each rectangle; spread to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Starting at longest side, roll up.
Cut each in half.

title: lemon-butter spritz cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Stir together flour and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Using a cookie press, shape into designs on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: plains special cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients, except preserves.
Shape mixture into ring.
Fill center with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup milk together.
Press 1/2 mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels; pour over cake.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over caramels.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Best when served warm.

title: butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Blend oil, garlic and tarragon in bowl.
Brush over lamb; let stand 2 hours to marinate.
Preheat broiler.
Place meat flat side down on shallow baking dish.
Brush with 1/2 mustard and broil 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn, brush with remaining mustard for 5 minutes.
Blend cheese, parsley and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over meat and pat to adhere.
Drizzle melted butter over meat.
Turn oven to 450°
and close door.
Bake for 20 minutes until crumbs brown on top.
Meat thermometer should register 130° rare.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.

title: ice cream with oreo cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, water and vanilla extract.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream. Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop from pan or peel off foil and slice.

title: orange basting sauce
directions: In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients.
Use a basting brush to coat.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add nutmeg.
Add buttermilk and the baking soda, which has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Sift the flour before measuring, then sift 3 times with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Dough will be fairly soft, but is manageable if your board is floured well.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
I use a wide mouth canning jar lid as a cookie cutter so as to make the large cookie.
Cut out and sprinkle sugar on top.
Use greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Layer in casserole dish. Top with potatoes.
Mix milk and soup; pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spring salad
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve flavored jello in hot water and add unflavored gelatin in dissolved also.
Add remaining cold water and chill until thickened.
Coat sliced bananas and apple with lemon juice.
Add other ingredients to thickened gelatin mixture and pour into 13 x 9-inch glass pan; chill until set.
Prepare Spring Salad Topping and spoon over gelatin.
Top with cheese.
Serves 12 to 20.

title: cranberry chiffon pie
directions: Over medium heat in a saucepan, melt the jellied cranberry sauce. Add the lemon juice and orange gelatin and bring to a boil. Remove from stove and when cool enough, refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Mix all beans, onion and pepper in large bowl.
In separate container, mix remaining ingredients. Pour over bean mixture.
Marinate overnight.
Stir several times. Serve chilled.
Keeps well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes in boiling water in a large saucepan about 1 minute.
Blend soup and milk in a small bowl.
Pour over potato mixture.
Dot with butter and cover.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Squeeze thawed spinach to get rid of excess water.
Set aside. Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Stir in spinach, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Let cool slightly.
In large mixing bowl, combine Ricotta, Feta cheese and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Stir in spinach mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can mix lemon juice with mayonnaise or cream cheese using mixer.
Good as a vegetable dip or with crackers.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients together.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour chilled dressing over entire top.
Cover with the bag of crushed chips. You may use as much lettuce, tomatoes and bell pepper as you desire.

title: pineapple stuffed pork chops
directions: Fill the chops, then brown them.
Pour drained pineapple juice over and bake in a slow oven.

title: hay stacks
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, melt chips; add noodles. Coat well.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order the eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients:
flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cucumbers and tomato salad
directions: Combine all and toss well to blend.
Drain and serve over leaf lettuce.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and continue beating until thick.
Add flour to egg mixture; fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: aunt betty's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add milk gradually.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into pie crusts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put the chicken in a large (1 1/2 to 2-quart) casserole dish. Pour the 2 cans of soup over the chicken.
Mix the eggs, onion, stuffing and the milk.
Pour the mixture over the chicken.
Drizzle a little chicken broth over the dressing to make it moist.
If getting brown before completely done, cover lightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve and enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line casserole with chicken; add water chestnuts over chicken. Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over chicken and chestnuts. Melt margarine and put cracker crumbs and poppy seed into melted margarine.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple and milk together.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Serve chilled or frozen.

title: caribbean rub
directions: Mix all together. Store in a jar.

title: dream cornbread
directions: Mix all together well and pour into a greased 9-inch skillet and bake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 6-quart saucepan stir together sugar and milk.
Add salt. Cook over medium-high heat to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium, stirring only 2 to 3 times, cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, peanut butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Place pan in cold water for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture starts losing its gloss.
Add walnuts; beat mixture until very thick.
Turn into 7 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: tasty onion sticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Trim crusts from bread.
Spread butter on bread.
Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: marinated wings
directions: Marinate wings overnight in Ziploc bag in mixture of soy sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Arrange in baking pan with marinade and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: saucy salisbury skillet
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into 4 oval patties.
In skillet, brown patties; pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for about 20 minutes or until done.
Stir and serve.
Quick, easy and very good.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. (Great with apples)

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix water and molasses; add alternating with dry ingredients, beating only enough to mix.
Drop from a spoon to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 315° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple in pan; spread evenly. Spread cherries on top of pineapple.
Spread cake mix over the fruits.
Spread nuts over top of cake mix.
Place squares of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in center and add remaining ingredients.
Blend well, for a medium firm dough. (if too sticky, add more flour).
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10-12 min.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Slice steak in 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown in margarine in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add beef broth and garlic.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and peppers. Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika and place in an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Dust top with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken stuffing balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend together egg, butter and liquid.
Stir in chicken, stuffing mix and cheese; mix until well blended.
Press and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheets and bake 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 2 or 3 times.
Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cocoa with milk.
Add vanilla and cream until smooth. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fruit combo
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit for 1 minute.
Layer fruit with the mixture.

title: fruit glaze
directions: Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Boil 1 minute.
While hot pour over fruit.
Refrigerate several hours uncovered.
Use chunk pineapple, 3 medium apples (red and green), bananas and mandarin oranges.

title: rye tasties
directions: Brown ground beef and pork; drain and cool.
Add grated cheese, oregano and Worcestershire.
Spread on rye squares.
Top with olives, mushrooms, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry custard
directions: Wash and hull the strawberries; slice them thin.
Place them in a bowl and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Blend the cornstarch to a smooth paste with a little milk; mix in the rest of the sugar and heat slowly in a pan with the rest of the milk and the well beaten eggs.
Stir in the vanilla and salt; cook slowly for 5 minutes, until the custard is thick.
Pour into a serving bowl and chill well.
When it's set, arrange the strawberries over the custard.

title: judi's shepherd pie
directions: Brown meat (can use turkey) with onion and mushrooms.
Spread in bottom of baking dish.
I like to use a big iron skillet.
Top the meat with a layer of frozen peas, a layer of Tater Tots and a layer of cheese.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cheese should be melted throughout. This dish is a favorite with kids!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yummy beans
directions: Mix beans with onion, brown sugar and liquid smoke.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger creams cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of soda, dissolved in 1/2 cup of water.
Sift in 3 heaping cupfuls of flour, salt, ginger and nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8+ minutes.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix
together
shortening, honey, egg and molasses.
In separate bowl
sift together dry ingredients.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured
surface.
Cut
with
cookie cutter.
Decorate with raisins, nuts, licorice and tiny candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and dice into small piece. Mix chicken, green onion, softened cream cheese, and 1 cup sour cream. Divide mixture and put in 10-12 flour tortillas, roll and place seam side down in a baking pan (spayed with Pam). When ready to bake, mix 1 cup sour cream and Rotel - pour over enchiladas to cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Then cover with the 2 cups of shredded cheese. Put back in the oven for 5-10 minutes or until cheese is melted. ENJOY!!

title: no cook divinity
directions: Beat dry frosting mix, corn syrup, water and vanilla together in small bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, until blended. Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until stiff peaks form (about 5 minutes). Transfer to large mixer bowl. Gradually blend in sugar on low speed or by hand. Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry at least 12 hours. Store in airtight container. Makes 5 to 6 dozen pieces. Can be frozen in airtight container for up to 2 months.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put 1 package jello in a small bowl with 2 cups hot water and stir.
Do the second package of jello the same way in another bowl.
Let each bowl of jello start to jell.
Have the cream cheese at room temperature.
Add carrots, pineapple, apple, pecans and salt to the first bowl of jello.
Put cheese into second bowl of jello, whip until very creamy.
Pour this bowl of jello mixture on top of the first bowl of jello.
Chill until firm and serve.

title: creamed celery-cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and cocoa; add to mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Be sure to use large eggs.

title: aunty dawn's "scrumptious" dessert
directions: You will need 1 large serving bowl.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add water, stirring constantly.
Add butter and salt.
Cook, stirring, until the mixture is very thick. Beat the egg yolks and add some of the mixture.
Return to the saucepan and cook 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add the lemon juice and rind, mixing it well, and pour the mixture into baked crust.
Make meringue.
Spread on pie, baking until lightly browned.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Mix pecans, flour and butter and spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over crust.
Slice strawberries on this layer; cover with glaze.
(You can put glaze, then strawberries if you prefer.)
Refrigerate about 4 hours.
Cut into pie wedges.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 4 tablespoons sugar and pat into 9 X 11 pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Prepare jello, using 1 3/4 cup boiling water.
Stir jello into frozen strawberries.
Chill until beginning to set.
Pour on top of cream layer and refrigerate until firm.
May use other flavors such as black cherry, raspberry, etc.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Butter or
spray
Pam
on
bottom
and sides of a large oblong baking dish.
Combine
potatoes, sour cream and soup in a large bowl;
salt and pepper
to	taste.	Put in baking dish and spread evenly.
Cover
top
with shredded cheese.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add shortening.
Mix with a fork. Mix separately the vinegar, egg and water.
Add to flour.
Chill 15 minutes.
Roll out.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 4 single crust pies.
May be frozen if well wrapped.

title: chicken and green noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water, 25 to 30 minutes, until tender. Drain, saving stock. Bone the chicken and cut meat into bite-sized pieces.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Put oil, self-rising flour and seasonings in skillet and stir over low heat until flour is brown.
Add tomatoes and water.
Stir. Place lid on skillet and simmer on low heat until consistency you like.
May have to add more water if too thick.

title: chicken stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low overnight.

title: biscuit topped casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and garlic in a Dutch oven until beef is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain in a colander.
Return beef mixture to Dutch oven and add remaining ingredients except beans, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Add beans; simmer, partially covered, 20 additional minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese chicken corn soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, corn and chicken in large saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Blend cornstarch with cold water and add to soup.
Continue cooking, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy; stir into soup.
Reduce heat and cook until foam is gone.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve hot.
One cup serving has 156 calories.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in a large heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, mustard and red pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, with wire whisk.
Gradually add milk and stir well. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 cup
Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup Swiss cheese, salt and pepper, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and honey together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in bananas. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot water. Mix until smooth.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce until smooth. Mix in 1/2 can onions, beans and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with the rest of the onions. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine sugar and flour and place on a shallow plate.
Dip both sides of each tomato slice into the mixture.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip tomato slices into egg mixture; then dip into bread crumbs.
In a skillet heat margarine and oil over medium-high heat.
Fry tomatoes until brown on each side.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into an angel food pan or Bundt pan.
Let set, covered, overnight.
Unmold.

title: oriental tidbits
directions: Combine all ingredients except crescent rolls.
Brown well until all pink disappears.
Separate crescent rolls.
Cut each section in half lengthwise with scissors.
Place 1 teaspoon mixture in triangle.
Roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
These may be frozen and heated in the microwave.

title: green enchiladas
directions: In double boiler, combine Velveeta cheese, soup, chiles, pimentos and milk.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Grate Longhorn cheese.
Chop onion.
Wrap the ground beef, cheese and onion in flour tortillas and pour the cheese mixture over this in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "yummy" barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in large pot; heat to blend in flavors.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon of sauce.

title: peanut butter muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until mildly lumpy.
Do not overmix. Spray 4 muffin pans with nonstick spray.
Fill 2/3 full. Partially fill remaining cups with water.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.

title: hamburger-cheese pie
directions: On ungreased cookie sheet take crescent rolls apart, arrange into a circle and seal edges.
Cook onion and hamburger until brown.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put layer of cheese on crust.
Add meat to top of cheese.
Bring edges over top.
Use leftover crescents to complete top of pie.
Seal completely.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Put in sand pail in layers pudding/crumbs/pudding, etc. End with crumbs on top to look like dirt. May add gummy worms (optional).

title: garden relish
directions: Chop cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion; combine vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
In a tight lid fitted jar, mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Shake well and pour over vegetables, tossing until well coated.
Refrigerate, covered, about 2 hours before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg nog
directions: Pour half of milk into bowl.
Add pudding; beat or shake 1 minute, or until it is smooth.
Add the rest of the milk, ice cream and flavorings.
Beat 1 minute more and serve.

title: beer cheese
directions: Beat cheeses at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth; add garlic and next 3 ingredients. Beat well. Gradually add beer; beat until blended. Chill 1 hour. Serve with crusty bread or crackers. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Cool.
Cut onion and bell pepper and mix with carrots.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.
Will keep up to 2 or 3 weeks.

title: zesty russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in screw-top jar.
Cover and shake well.
Chill before serving.

title: oklahoma potatoes
directions: Rinse potatoes thoroughly.
Cut into French fries leaving peel on.
Place in heavy duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with seasoning and put a generous amount of butter in the packet.
Seal carefully. Place over coals and cook for about 15 minutes or until tender. Great with grilled hamburgers, steak, etc.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Serve with carrot sticks, celery and cauliflower.

title: egg & cheese brunch
directions: Mix.
Bake in 9x13-inch pan at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Can be made the night before and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Sift flours, salt and baking soda together into a large bowl. Stir in oats.
Make a well in the center.

Pour in buttermilk and stir with a wooden spoon until mixture comes together to form a soft, moist dough (if dry, add a few tablespoons of buttermilk). Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and form it into a large, rounded disk about 8 inches in diameter.
Cut a deep cross through the dough with a sharp knife, cutting the disk almost in quarters.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in large bowl until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Hold cupcakes, top sides down, in palm of hand.
Spread Cool Whip mixture on bottom and sides.
Press coconut onto frosting.
Place cupcakes, top sides down, on serving platter.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Makes 24.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and serve with your favorite crackers or chips.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Cut tamales lengthwise; line pan.
Saute oil and onions.
Add chicken, chiles, tomato sauce, water, salt, oregano, corn, olives and sour cream.
Pour over tamales and top with cheese.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly mix real mayonnaise and flour in saucepan.
Gradually blend in broth, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Mix in chicken.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: james polk's poke sallet
directions: Select tender young polk greens and some tender stalks, not over 6 or 7 inches tall.
Cut the stalks into small pieces and clean the greens well, rinsing several times.
Parboil and discard the water.
Add fresh water and cook until almost tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add greens, salt and chopped onions to the bacon drippings.
Cook over low heat for about 25 minutes.
Serve with fried salt pork and corn pone.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Stir in sugar, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Blend together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix with first ingredients and stir in nuts.
Spread batter in greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix crabmeat with cream cheese.
Place on platter.
Make depression in middle of dip and pour cocktail sauce into it. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican hot nuts
directions: Combine the nuts and melted butter and toss until the nuts are evenly coated.
Spread in a baking pan and bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix the chili and cumin together in a bowl.
Add the nuts and stir well to coat.
Return the nuts to the baking pan and bake for another ten minutes.
Drain on paper towels before serving.
Makes four cups.

title: angel food cake strawberry dessert
directions: Line bottom of a large baking dish with cake pieces.
Stir boiling water into gelatin pieces in a medium bowl until dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour over cake pieces.
Top with strawberries, saving some for garnish.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Stir together crushed wafers and butter.
Press mixture evenly over the bottom and 1-inch up the side of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place the pan in a shallow baking pan.

title: jill's favorite dessert
directions: Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: golden mandarin bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Heat mandarin juice just to lukewarm. Add sugar, salt, mandarin peel and butter.
Add egg, half of flour and softened yeast.
Beat until well blended and thick.
Add remaining flour and mix to moderately stiff dough.
Turn out and knead lightly on floured board just until dough smoothes out and forms ball.
Cover with dampened cloth; let rest 20 minutes.

title: syrup pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 whole egg until creamy.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and syrup.
Beat well and add melted butter.
Mix thoroughly and then add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. For the first 15 minutes, cook at 375°, then cook at 300° until pie is firm.
Remove from the stove.
Make meringue and spread on pie.

title: bachelor's pie
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper and beef in a large skillet.
Brown slowly, stirring constantly.
Do not burn.
When lightly browned, add flour; mix well.
Add carrots and milk.
Stir until hot.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes; spread to cover.
(Use your leftover mashed potatoes and roast beef.)
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tuna melts
directions: Combine tuna, salad dressing, vegetables and pepper.
Mix. Spread on muffin halves and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese begins to melt.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: glazed orange loaf cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl and add all ingredients, except eggs and orange rind.
Beat with mixer 2 minutes, then add eggs and orange rind and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake filling
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook slow, stirring constantly.
When thickens, add vanilla.
Cook before you bake cake, then it will be ready to put on baked cake.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix together in a saucepan. Add juice from large can crushed pineapple. Cook until thickened. Add crushed pineapple and spread over yellow cake or between layers of coconut cake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
This recipe makes 3 (9-inch) pies and freezes well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into pot.
Constantly stirring, boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and nuts, stirring briskly.
Spoon cookies onto wax paper.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 1/2 cup of water to boiling.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Do not drain.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook and stir about 4 minutes or until heated through.
Add more milk if too thick for your liking.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, boiling water and margarine and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Add to the oatmeal mixture and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix self-rising flour, margarine and pecans and pat it out in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and let it cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix as for any casserole; bake on low in oven about 1 hour. Top casserole with cheese when nearly done.
Bake just long enough to melt cheese.

title: 24 karat cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter; add the egg and beat. Beat in honey and then the carrots.
On low speed, add dry ingredients and then the oatmeal.
When thoroughly mixed, stir in raisins and walnuts.
Place dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Cookies are done when golden colored and the tops spring back if touched with fingertips.

title: bacon swirls
directions: Combine cooked bacon, mushrooms and mayonnaise.
Stir well. Set aside.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations together to seal at seams.
Spread softened cream cheese over each rectangle leaving 1/4 inch margin on one long side and no margins on other sides.
Spread 1/4 bacon mixture evenly over cream cheese.
Roll dough up jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seams to seal.
Place in freezer to chill for easier cutting.
Remove and cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Brush each slice with egg white and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes until lightly browned.
Yield:
36 appetizers.

title: cracker chicken
directions: Combine milk and eggs and mix well.
Roll chicken in flour mixture; dip in egg batter.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Cook until brown; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes longer. Remove lid; turn heat back up to crisp.

title: walnut delecta "bites"
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Gradually stir in flour and walnuts.
Chill dough.
Shape into marble size balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until firm, but not brown.
Roll gently in 10x sugar.
Cool; roll again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Mix browned hamburger, corn and green beans in casserole dish. Add mushroom soup diluted with a little water.
Mix well. Cover top of casserole with cheese slices.
Layer Tater Tots over cheese slices.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients. Add eggs, milk and honey. Mix. Add margarine. Mix well. Grease pan with Pam or oil. Pour mix into pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna salad mold
directions: Heat undiluted chicken rice soup and gelatin until dissolved. Fold in mayonnaise, tuna and celery.
Pour into mold; refrigerate and enjoy!

title: peach coogan
directions: Blend margarine into cake mix.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake this mixture for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put peaches on top.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Also, add nuts if you want.
Take egg and beat it into sour cream; drizzle over top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. You can also make this with other kinds of fruit.
Great with blueberries.

title: arroz caldo(chicken rice soup)
directions: Wash chicken and dry with paper towel.
In a big (3-quart) saucepan, heat oil; saute garlic until brown.
Add onions and ginger; saute 3 minutes more.
Add chicken, salt, m.s.g. and patis.
Saute until chicken is light brown.
Add rice; cook, stirring, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil. Lower heat and cook, covered, for 30 minutes or until the chicken is tender.
Add a dash of pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and garnish with green onions and toasted garlic chips, if desired.

title: hamburger and cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef 'n broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, combine steak sauce, soy sauce and garlic. Pour marinade over steak in a nonmetal dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade; reserve marinade.
In a large lightly oiled skillet over medium-high heat, stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until steak is no longer pink.
Remove steak with a slotted spoon; keep warm.

title: fluttering butterflies
directions: Butter a large baking sheet.
For the base of each butterfly, sprinkle about 1/2 teaspoon nuts in a small circle on a baking sheet.
Measure 2 inches between circles.
Make each butterfly's wings by arranging 2 pretzels together on top of nuts.
Set aside baking sheet.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Mix eggs, milk and seasoning well. Toss cheese in flour.
Add to milk and egg mixture along with bacon.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: kraut (homemade)
directions: In sterilized quart jars, pack cabbage (not tight).
Drain excess water.
Heat water, vinegar and salt, but not boiling. Pour over cabbage and seal.
Store in a dark place for 3 or 4 weeks.

title: warm salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, egg, salt and pepper.
Add to hot bacon grease and heat to boiling.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour warm dressing over lettuce.
Sprinkle bacon bits over lettuce.

title: orange-cream dessert
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon peel, 1/2 cup orange juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Add 1 cup orange juice; cool.
Drizzle over top, bottom and sides of cake.
Combine whipping cream with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon orange peel. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into the sour cream until blended.
Spread evenly over top and sides of cake.
Chill several hours.
(Sour cream in the frosting gives an unusual tang.)

title: apricot-stuffed chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop; season with salt and pepper.
Combine corn, crumbs, onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt, thyme and sage.
Spoon the stuffing lightly into chops.
Arrange chops in single layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain syrup from apricots into medium saucepan; stir in steak sauce and the 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil uncovered until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Stud apricots with cloves. Uncover chops (do not turn) and bake 45 minutes longer.
Add apricots to baking dish.
Brush chops and apricots with glaze. Bake uncovered 25 minutes more.

title: arista di maiale(italian roast pork)
directions: Marinate the pork loin in the oil, garlic, rosemary, bay leaf, white wine, salt and pepper for 2 to 3 hours.
Place loin on a rack in a roasting pan, season with more salt and pepper and baste it with the marinade.
Roast at 450° for 15-20 mins. until browned. Turn heat down to 300° and roast for 45 mins. to 1 hour.
Internal temp. should be 135° on meat thermometer.
Baste with marinade frequently during roasting.
You can put sauerkraut or potatoes or both in the pan under the rack to cook in the pork juices.
(I use new potatoes cut in half.)

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add flour and potato chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cookies do not spread when baked so you can put them close together.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in a sealed container. Add to hot water in amount to suit your taste. Will stay indefinitely in a sealed container.

title: chill-chasing chili
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Crumble sausage and beef into 4-quart casserole.
Stir in onion and garlic.
Cook, covered, on high 8 to 10 minutes until meat loses its pink color, stirring twice during cooking.
Spoon off and discard drippings.
Into casserole, stir tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on high 20 to 24 minutes until peppers are tender; stir twice during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dough enhancer
directions: Blend Vitamin C tablets, then add other ingredients with lecithin last.
Blend together well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and milk; mix until smooth.
Add oats and stir until mixed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, pepper and onions; crush noodles and mix all together.
Add sugar, vinegar, oil flavor packages and pour over broccoli mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight, will keep a week.
The longer it sets the better it gets.

title: plum jelly
directions: Wash and stem plums.
Add 1 cup water to 1 quart fruit.
Bring to a boil.
Add 3 to 4 cups sugar to 1 quart of fruit juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Simmer 20 minutes until jelly stage is reached.

title: deep fried camembert cheese
directions: The cheese must be cold.
Cut Camembert into small wedges. Lightly coat wedges in flour.
Dip each wedge in slightly beaten eggs and coat in bread crumbs, then refrigerate.
Cheese can be prepared several hours before frying.
Fry until golden in very hot cooking oil for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain briefly on paper towels.
Serve hot as cocktail snack or as a light dessert with toast and your favorite jam.

title: spiced cider
directions: Heat cider to boiling point.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and simmer in cider for 3 minutes.
May be served at once or cooled and reheated when needed.

title: apple-pear salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together yogurt and cranberry-orange sauce.
Place in freezer for 10 minutes to chill. Core and cut pear into wedges, then core and cut apple into wedges on lettuce-lined plates.
Dollop with chilled yogurt mixture.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate snowflake cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Cover with crumbs.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° until crumbs brown.

title: sweet potato fries
directions: Clean the sweet potatoes, but do not peel. Cut into strips like French Fries.
Spray cookie sheet and arrange "fries" in a single layer.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender, turning half-way through, and re-spraying.
Serve with honey or maple syrup (not ketchup)!

title: sephardic spinach pie (kosher for passover)
directions: Place the spinach in a large mixing bowl and let stand until completely thawed. Do not drain. Add eggs, cheese, oil and meal and mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and syrup.
Heat until sugar is almost dissolved.
Beat eggs until light.
Mix eggs and sugar mixture real well.
Add dash of salt.
Put pecans in pie shell.
Carefully pour syrup over pecans.
Pecans will come to top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 40 minutes more or until done.

title: chewy maple walnut drops
directions: Boil syrup to 254°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then slowly add syrup in thin stream to egg whites.
Beat until it loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Add walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Allow to dry.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup crushed cornflakes over all.
Bake as hash browns at 375° for 1 hour.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: Parboil green beans for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until tender.
Cook bacon crisp; remove from pan.
Leave 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings and cook onion until lightly browned.
Put in with beans and add potatoes.
Cook slowly 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Should not have a lot of liquid.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Chop ingredients except for cheese very fine.
Mix and drain. Set aside.
Lay out tortillas and divide cheese.
Spread evenly among them.
Spread cheese to cover tortillas.
Sprinkle vegetables evenly among tortillas.
Roll up tortillas as tight as possible.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut tortillas in 1/2-inch slices.

title: farris walton's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Cream together the butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour.
Mix flavorings in last.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion, celery, cabbage and carrot in butter for 10 minutes.
Add the hash browns, broth, water and sausage (cut up); cook until vegetables are done.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef and onion (or microwave on High for 3 minutes). Drain well.
In medium mixing bowl, beat together milk, mayonnaise and seasoning. Stir in beaten eggs. Add 1 cup cheese and ground beef and onion mixture to bowl.
Pour into baked pie shell in glass pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool.
Cut up.
Chop onion; add to potatoes. Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain; cool, crumble and add to potato mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, heat cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Pour over potato mixer and mix well. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except mayonnaise, water, eggs and potato chips.
Combine mayonnaise and water; add to mixture.
Add chopped eggs.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven, uncovered, until bubbly hot.

title: chruscziki(or angels wings)
directions: Put whiskey into the grease in a deep fryer (be careful).
Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Then add flour to roll dough.
Roll the dough paper thin and cut in strips, 1 1/2 inches wide and 3 inches long.
Slit in the middle and twist each piece.
Put into the grease and turn when browned.
Dry on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: creamed eggs, peas and carrots
directions: Cook peas and carrots according to directions on package. Drain.
Save liquid.
Combine vegetable liquid and water, soup, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Add peas and carrots.
Add eggs; mix gently to avoid breaking up eggs.
Heat until mixture is bubbling hot, stirring only as necessary to prevent sticking. Serve over toast.

title: paradise salad
directions: To jello, add 1 cup water and let come to a boil.
Melt marshmallows in this.
Add pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, cheese and pecans.
Let congeal until thick, stirring occasionally.
When thick and cold, fold in whipped cream.
Stir. Let become set in refrigerator and unmold.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk, shortening and mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° in round pans 30 to 35 minutes, in 9 x 13-inch pan, 45 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt butter, making sure butter does not brown.
As soon as butter starts to melt, add garlic and herbs.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and mix well with a whisk.
Simmer over low heat to allow flavors to blend, about 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until opaque, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheater potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and set aside. Use 3 tablespoons drippings to saut onion. Add potatoes and water and cook 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Blend in all other ingredients except bacon pieces and parsley. Do not boil. Add crumbled bacon and parsley and serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together the margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Bring to a hard boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda and stir well.
While foaming, pour over popped corn, stirring to coat all popcorn.
Do in a large roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: creamy crunchy chicken 'n rice
directions: Combine cheese and hot rice.
Add chicken, cooked peas and half of the onions, mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes.
(This recipe does well substituting 1 pound browned hamburger for the chicken.)

title: tangy chicken with tomatoes and herbs
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion, garlic and herbs in oil until onion is tender-crisp.
Stir in tomatoes and next five ingredients.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender. Thicken sauce with cornstarch and water mixture.
Serve chicken and sauce with noodles.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: toasted crabmeat rounds
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat with a fork or your fingers and set aside.
Put all the remaining ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 20 seconds, stopping to scrape down the sides of the blender.
Combine and mix together the sauce and crabmeat.
Pile on whole wheat or rye bread rounds and sprinkle top with paprika.
Broil until crabmeat starts to brown, around 7 minutes.
Remove from broiler.
Place on serving dish and serve immediately.
Makes 1 cup or about 16 rounds.

title: broccoli, asparagus or cauliflower soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in flour. Cook 3 minutes over low heat; stir constantly.
Cool.
Set aside. If using broccoli, wash and trim off tough part.
Separate and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: peach melba pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Cool. Chill. In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 1 cup of cheese mixture on bottom of prepared pastry shell.
Spoon chilled raspberry mixture evenly on top.
Spoon remaining cheese filling over raspberries.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: norwegian almond bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, almond extract, butter and egg yolk.
Mix at low speed until particles are fine.
Reserve 1/2 cup and press remaining mixture into 9-inch square pan.
Combine almonds, confectioners sugar, egg whites and water to make a paste.
Carefully spread paste over bottom layer.
Crumble reserved mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Especially good during the Christmas holidays.

title: hot tamale loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, then put one layer of it in bottom of pan. Then a thin layer of meal softened with water and salted to taste. Keep alternating until all mixture is used.
Bake one hour in slow oven.

title: linguini in peanut sauce
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions; drain.
In separate bowl, combine hot water and peanut butter.
Stir in soy sauce, vinegar, scallions, garlic, sugar and red pepper; mix well. Combine drained pasta with sauce; toss well.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: fish casserole
directions: Pour over fish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Can use cherry or orange jello.

title: old fashioned fruit stack cake
directions: mix all ingredients together, Pour out on floured cloth and knead together as would biscuits.

Then tear off large enough dough pieces and make a ball and press into a greased 8-inch cake pan. Make your cake layers thin, cook on 350 degrees until done, continue this method until all the dough has been baked.
Stack the cooled cake layers and put your cooked apples in between each layer.
Stack as high as you want.

title: monkey bread
directions: After bread is thawed, cut into 20 pieces (any way you want). Melt butter/margarine.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and pecans in bowl. Dip dough in butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Stack alternately in tube or Bundt pan or lay in 9 x 7-inch pan. Sprinkle any leftover mixture and butter over dough.
Cover and put in warm place.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out on plate immediately after baking.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300° or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Use tube pan to bake cake in.

title: lasagna
directions: Remove the sausage meat from outer casings (ground pork can be substituted); chop the meat. In 5-quart pan, over medium heat, saute sausage or pork, beef, onion and garlic until well browned, about 20 minutes.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Put bread on a cookie sheet. Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve on a Caesar salad or a salad bar.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar and set
aside.
Mix together milk and instant pudding and add Cool Whip.
Then
blend	the cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together.

title: favorite son-in-love cherry delight
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Serve cold.

title: country supper
directions: Fry sliced potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in oil over low heat in heavy skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
When carrots and potatoes are tender, place sausage on top.
Cover; heat about 12 minutes.

title: fresh orange juice pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Beat 1 egg at a time in mixture of Crisco and sugar.
Add flour gradually.
Mix the juice and vanilla with the cake batter.
Pour batter into a greased and lightly floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and have ready. Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs, alternately with orange juice and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 batter into tube pan, then spread 1/2 of apples over batter.
Repeat with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peppercorn steak with mushrooms
directions: Press cracked pepper into both sides of steak; saute with 2 teaspoons margarine in a nonstick skillet.
Add noodles, 2 teaspoons margarine, tomatoes, onion and reduced-calorie salad dressing.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: african peanut chicken soup
directions: Cook onion, pepper and garlic until onions begin to brown. Add tomatoes, juice, broth and pepper (red and black).
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour; add rice and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until rice is tender.
Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Add salt to taste.
Makes 9 cups, 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma's custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar, then beat in flour.
Beat well. Add vanilla and salt, then milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until done.
Top with beaten egg whites made into meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, vinegar, grated lemon peel, garlic, salt, pepper and basil (makes about 1 cup marinade). Put chicken in shallow baking dish and cover with marinade. Marinate chicken, turning once, for 30 to 45 minutes or overnight. Refrigerate until ready to cook.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix croutons and milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mash until smooth.
Add to meat.
Add rest of ingredients except gravy.
Mix well.
Shape into small meat balls.
Place in single layer in shallow pan.
Pour gravy over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
I use Heinz gravy.

title: macho nachos
directions: Stir 1 teaspoon Tabasco sauce into the bean dip and spread on chips. Sprinkle with cheese and microwave until softened.
Top with guacamole dip and sour cream.
Garnish liberally with sliced Trappey's jalapenos.

title: venison spread
directions: Grind first four ingredients together.
Then take the ground mixture and mix in enough Miracle Whip to make spreadable.
Add mustard and enough salt for flavor.
Makes excellent spread for sandwiches.

title: cornish game hen with grapes(microwave)
directions: Place grapes and broth in a 10 x 7 x 4-inch oval dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Place split hen, skin side up, over grapes. Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.
Cook at 100% for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 2.

title: spring salad
directions: Crush graham crackers; add butter and line bottom of pan. Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add condensed milk, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix together.
Beat whipping cream until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour over crumbs.
Let set overnight.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard, salt and pepper to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for several days.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sugar cookies(makes about 3 dozen)
directions: Cream butter; mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour and baking soda.
Mix good.
Put in Frigidaire for 2 hours or overnight.
On well floured board, roll out a small amount at a time to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out cookies with whatever cutter you want.
I used cookie Easter cutters and also a round cutter.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook 2 small packages of frozen mixed vegetables according to directions on packages.
Don't overcook.
Drain and mix with above. Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread on top.
Melt stick of margarine and pour on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry supreme salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Gradually add lemon Jell-O.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Spread over cherry layer.
Top with nuts.
Chill until firm.
This also looks pretty made in a Jell-O mold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs.
Mix all together and drop by tablespoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take off pan with spatula and place on wood cutting board or brown paper bag.

title: chicken chasseur
directions: Combine flour, oregano, salt and pepper.
Reserve 1 tablespoon mixture; coat chicken with remaining mixture.
In oven-going skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Combine wine and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Add onion.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Keep warm.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and sugar to mixture in skillet. Cook about 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend reserved flour mixture and 1/4 cup cold water; add to sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Pour over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and cut with scissors.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; add vinegar and water, stirring until smooth.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in corn, pepper and pimento.
Cover and chill.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils; cook in the water.
Add rest of ingredients and seasoning except salt and McKay's seasoning.
Cook on low heat until done, 1 hour or so.
Blend all ingredients except 2 cups. Add milk as you blend to make thick soup.
If soup thickens too much, add a little water.
Put in crock-pot to keep hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, peppers and onion and drain.
Add all other ingredients except cracker crumbs and put into casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and a few pats of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Fold in noodles and top with almonds.
Bake in 270° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon rush
directions: Mix oleo and flour as for pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: dessert
directions: Mix everything together and freeze in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and egg.
Combine milk, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake in muffin cups at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Do not frost.
Best served slightly warm.
Kids love them.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Combine ingredients several hours before serving; chill.

title: zucchini and squash slaw
directions: Cut vegetables to matchstick size.
Mix spices, oil, mustard and vinegar with whisk.
Add vegetables and toss to coat. Refrigerate until served.

title: christmas bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, oil and milk.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add egg mixture; mix just until thoroughly combined.
Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and nuts.
Turn into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with chicken that has been boned.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread on top of chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with broth. Mix with stuffing mix.
Spread stuffing mix on top of chicken soup.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla, egg and egg white.
Cut apples into cubes and put in a pan.
Put combined mixture ove the top of the apples.
Melt stick of butter and pour all of it over the top.
Put a very generous amount of cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and topping is browned and crisp.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips; spread over top of mixture.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: asparagus parmesan
directions: Place asparagus in 2-quart microwave casserole.
Cook, uncovered, 9 to 12 minutes on High.
Drain well.
Gently toss asparagus with butter to coat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes on Medium.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: walnut applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and spices.
Add shortening and egg; beat well. Stir in applesauce and vanilla.
Add flour with soda, salt and baking powder; beat smooth.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: curry rice
directions: Mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour through a funnel into a 2-inch deep (4-quart) pan filled with hot oil (370°).
Fry until light brown, then place on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: gretchen mather's fresh pickles(about 1 quart)
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice quite thin, about 1/16 of an inch. Place in stainless or glass bowl with onion and green pepper. Toss with salt and mustard seed.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain off as much juice as possible without losing seeds.
Mix vinegar and sugar while cucumbers are standing so that sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with a relish tray or use as an ingredients in sandwiches.

title: special occasion egg nog
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in scalded milk and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Cook over boiling water on low heat until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and cool quickly. Stir in vanilla.
Cover, refrigerate until serving time.
At serving time, beat until smooth and frothy.
Stir in half and half.
Put in punch bowl.
Float scoops of ice cream on top.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; add nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix in order given, folding in beaten egg whites last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 40 minutes.

title: praline pecan cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or three small loaf pans. Sprinkle some of the pecans on bottom of pan. Mix all ingredients except frosting.
Beat two minutes. Fold in frosting. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grilled mixed vegetables
directions: Tear off 4 large squares of foil and place 1/4 of vegetables on each piece of foil.
Melt margarine, add cheese and seasonings, and pour over vegetables on foil.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Seal tightly and grill over medium hot coals 15 minutes on a side.

title: bread crumb pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg, Karo and buttermilk, mixed with soda, then raisins and nuts mixed with flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Then add bread crumbs.
Mix all together well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold.
Lemon Sauce is optional.

title: angel hair with savory tomato sauce
directions: In skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.

title: white sauce with spaghetti
directions: Cook cloves of garlic in olive oil in frying pan.
Add green olives and half and half.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cooked pasta; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate doughnuts
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together except add flour slowly. Fry in frying pan at 375°.
Use lard for frying.	Fill frying pan 3/4 full
of melted lard (2 pounds roughly).
May have to add more during cooking.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cook in salted, boiling water.
Mash until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until light and fluffy. Place in greased casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast roll
directions: Prepare cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Brown sausage; drain.
Scramble eggs.
Carefully unroll the Pillsbury Pipin' Hot loaf on the cookie sheet.
Spoon the sausage, eggs and cheese onto the loaf.
Roll the loaf back up, carefully sealing the top seam as well as the ends of the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat until thick first 4 ingredients.
Stir in the zucchini and pineapple.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and stir gently into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Divide batter into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack and cool.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Thaw peas and drain off excess water.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill until ready to serve.

title: sinfully delicious cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch Pyrex glass baking dish.

title: microwave brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole. Microwave 4 minutes; stir.
Add nuts.
Microwave 4 minutes more. Stir in butter and vanilla, blending well until nuts are lightly brown and syrup is very hot.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir gently until distributed well and it's foamy throughout.
Pour onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet to cool before breaking into bite-sized pieces.

title: cheese and fruit squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, oleo and salt like a pie crust.
Add in cheese and egg mixture.
Press 3/4 dough on a medium cookie sheet.
Top with jam.
Roll the other 1/4 out and cut into strips. Lattice on top of filling and sear edges.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Put in refrigerator for 20 minutes.

title: buster bar torte
directions: Mix together cookies and oil. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Chill until firm. Slice ice cream and spread on cookie crust. Top with 1 cup Spanish peanuts. Freeze.

title: maydell's cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers in 1/2-inch strips.
Soak 8 hours or overnight in a large pot (not aluminum) with the lime and water, then rinse with cold water; let stand 15 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove from water.
Cool. Debone and tear meat into pieces.
Melt butter in large saucepan. Stir in flour.
Cook.
Stir until golden brown.
Add vegetables and chicken broth.
Cook vegetables until tender and gumbo is thick.
Add chicken, rice, parsley and sugar.
Season to taste. Serves 6.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: peanut delight
directions: Combine flour and butter or oleo; add peanuts.
Press evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: hershey almond bar pie
directions: Microwave almond bars until melted (be careful not to burn), stirring constantly.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into crust. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with slivered almonds.

title: pizza on a stick
directions: Mix melted margarine, oregano and basil.
Cut pizza dough in strips and twist.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until melted.

title: granola
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spread on shallow roasting pan.

title: carol's chicken casserole(creamy chicken on biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas under running cold water to separate.
Heat peas, chicken soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to just boiling in saucepan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Keep warm while preparing biscuits.
Stir Bisquick and water to soft dough.
Beat 20 strokes.
Smooth into a ball.
Knead 5 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with 2-inch cutter.
Pour chicken mixture into oblong dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put biscuits on cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix dry ingredients and oil.
Place crackers in large bowl. Add oil mixture and stir until all crackers are oil coated.
Shake well in clean paper bag to absorb surplus oil.

title: apple-raisin ladybugs for 2
directions: Place lettuce leaves on two salad plates.
Arrange 2 apple quarters, peel side up, on lettuce.
Use dabs of peanut butter to place raisins in space between apple quarters.
Place 1 grape at the stem end of apple for head.
For legs, cut the remaining grapes lengthwise into 4 pieces; place 3 on each side of ladybugs. Place small dabs of peanut butter on remaining raisins; gently press on apples for spots.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put 1/2 bag crumbled chips on bottom of 8 x 12-inch casserole. Brown hamburg and onion, drain.
Add tomato sauce, nacho cheese soup and taco seasoning mix.
Cook until boiling.
Spoon over chips in pan.
Spread sour cream over top.
Put grated cheese on then other 1/2 bag chips on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and grated orange rind, then add sweet milk, salt and nutmeg.
Mix.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda and add flour (enough to handle).
Add vanilla.

title: marinated mushrooms and broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets; cut in bite-size pieces.
Trim and discard tough stalk ends.
Peel remaining stalks and stems, then cut diagonally into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place on a rack over boiling water in a pan (about 5 quarts).
Cover and steam on high heat until barely tender-crisp, 1 or 2 minutes.
Immerse in ice water until cold.
Drain well.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, milk and cooking oil.
Stir in onion, cheese and peppers.
Bake at 450° in a greased jelly roll pan.
Remove from oven when nicely browned and tests done with a toothpick.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fabulous carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple well, pressing out excess syrup with back of spoon. Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs until blended.
Beat in pineapple, carrots, raisins and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Beat small amounts of dry ingredients into pineapple mixture until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Frost.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Put all other ingredients in bowl.
Pour dressing over and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: bran bread
directions: Put in bread maker in order listed.
Push button for white bread or mix in a large bowl; knead until elastic.
Let rise. Punch down and knead 3 minutes.
Let rise; form into 2 loaves. Put in bread pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate dipped cherries
directions: Drain cherries thoroughly and place on paper toweling.
Mix together butter, syrup and salt.
Blend in sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Chill, if too soft.
Wrap about 1 teaspoon of fondant evenly around each cherry.
Roll in palm of hand to smooth surface.
Place on waxed paper on a baking sheet.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate in small saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Holding cherries by stem, dip one at a time in chocolate. Place on waxed paper on baking sheet and chill until firm.
Store in covered container in the fridge.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Combine flour, seasonings and soda.
Add and mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Use Pam and spray in a Bundt pan or you can use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange balls(frozen)
directions: Cream powdered sugar, orange juice and butter.
Add vanilla wafers and pecans.
Form into balls; roll in coconut.
Freeze. Serve frozen.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Cook shredded beef in oleo until edges curl.
Remove beef. Blend flour into oleo; gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add beef and mix well.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon over crisp chow mein noodles or hot toast.

title: slice and bake chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts. Divide dough into quarters. On waxed paper, shape each quarter into a 9-inch roll. Roll in the waxed paper. Refrigerate up to 1 week or freeze up to 8 weeks.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add oleo.
Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Add to vegetables.
Add clams last; simmer 5 minutes, just until thickened.

title: karaai gosh(beef stew)
directions: Cook meat on slow fire, stirring all the time, until the water has evaporated, then add all the ingredients; cook until meat is tender and gravy is thick.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage coarsely; fry in bacon drippings, covered, for 30 minutes or until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with clean hands.
Chill dough. Roll out 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares or shapes using cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
The tops should not be brown.

title: fudge filled peanut butter bar
directions: Combine dry cake mix, peanut butter, butter and eggs.
Stir until well mixed.
Press 2/3 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Reserve the rest for topping.

title: perfect fudge
directions: In a heavy, large saucepan, put sugar and evaporated milk. Bring slowly to a rolling boil.
Let it boil for no longer than 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips and butter or margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add nutmeats and vanilla.
Spread on a large ungreased pan and when cool, cut into squares.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss pasta, cooked with dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add assorted chopped raw vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Rinse beans with cold water and drain. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine beans, peppers, corn, tomatoes, dip, Cheddar cheese, chili powder and cumin.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Boil laundry starch.
Pour into several jars.
Mix a little poster paint with the starch.

title: cheese-filled cucumber slices
directions: Cut off ends of cucumber.
Using tines of a fork, score peel of cucumber.
Cut in half crosswise, removing and discarding seeds with a melon baller or small spoon; set aside.

title: army cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well. Watch for lumps in the brown sugar and throw away any lumps.

Add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well after each addition. Place in rolls on waxed paper in the freezer and use as needed. Makes 15 to 20 rolls (depends on your size roll) or 30 dozen. To bake, place by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes (no longer).

title: banana split
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs and butter; press into buttered 12 x 9 x 1 1/2 pan.

Into mixer, add powdered sugar, eggs, soft margarine, vanilla and rum extract; beat for 5 minutes. Spread over crust and chill, then slice bananas lengthwise over cream mixture. Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Whip Dream Whip; spread on top and garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until soft. Stir in flour. Add water and cook until thickened. Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce with broccoli and eggs. Blend well. Place in greased dish. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and combine with 1/2 cup bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut broiled yams
directions: Cook yams until tender, but not soft.
Two (1-lb.) cans can be substituted.
Cut yams in half and arrange in lightly greased, shallow 2-qt. casserole.
Top with 1 cup coconut.
Combine butter, brown sugar and cream; mix well and pour over yams.
Top with remaining coconut and cherries.
Broil 5-inches from heat for 5 minutes or until coconut is light golden brown.

title: turkey chop suey
directions: Drain the vegetables, reserving liquid.
In a large saucepan, saute onion in a tablespoon of margarine until translucent.
Add turkey, bouillon, water, teriyaki and Worcestershire sauce. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup of water until mixed well.
Add to turkey mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add vegetables. Heat until warmed through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: crumb-topped blueberry cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir well.
In large measuring cup, combine eggs, milk, butter and lemon juice.
Stir liquid ingredients into flour mixture until blended.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle blueberries evenly over batter.
Sprinkle with Crumb Topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour. Mix. Add buttermilk, bananas and nuts.
Mix all.
Pour into two loaf pans sprayed with Pam or greased.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and serve with cauliflower or celery sticks, or any other vegetable.

title: country sausage and potatoes
