directions: Cook sausage and onion until browned.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix and water.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots; cover and simmer 10 more minutes. Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 more minutes until broccoli is heated and cheese is melted.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Separate dough into eight rectangles; firmly press perforations together to seal.
Spread each rectangle with 2 rounded measuring tablespoonfuls cream cheese mixture.
Cut each rectangle in half diagonally; repeat with opposite corners.
Cut in half crosswise to form six triangles.
Roll up triangles, starting at short ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet; brush with combined egg and water.
Sprinkle with poppy seed, if desired.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in beaten egg; coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in greased shallow baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 13x9x2-inch pan.
Melt butter and peanut butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese spread(lo-cal)
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese and oleo until light.
Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Add onions and bell peppers. Add chili powder, kidney beans, and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: bool go-kee chicken(korean barbecue)
directions: Combine sugar, pepper, sesame seeds, water, soy sauce, sesame oil, ginger, garlic, and scallions. Mix well. Add meat and marinate several hours or overnight.
This is a very flexible recipe. Once marinated, the meat can be grilled, broiled, or stir-fried. Beef or pork can be subsituted with good results.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream milk and lemon juice.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Add flour and baking soda; mix well. Roll into 1 inch balls and roll in sugar. Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Flatten in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Do not over bake as this will cause the cookies to be hard when cooled. Cool on wire racks.

title: award winning sugar cookies
directions: Heat over to 350°. Beat butter, shortening and sugar together. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda and stir into butter mixture a little at a time. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in additional sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten them slightly with the bottom of a glass. Bake for 10-12 minutes. Cool on rack. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and vegetable oil.
Add chocolate chips, etc. if desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spray baking sheets with Pam before placing cookies on to bake.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets; save juice.
Boil 1/2 cup water; add beet juice, salt and 1/3 cup vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling mixture.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar; let set until syrupy.
Add diced beets, chopped onion and celery.
Add horseradish, if desired (this gives an entirely different flavor to salad).
Pour into a shallow, square pan.
After congealed, may spread with softened cream cheese.

title: heavenly pudding cake
directions: Cut cake in half.
Tunnel out middle of bottom of cake. Crumble cut out portion into a large bowl.
Make pudding following directions on box.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip and mix.
Add to crumbled cake.
Pour or spoon into tunneled portion of cake.
Replace top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Split the chicken breasts in halves.
Place in soup kettle and cover with water.
Add bay leaves, celery, some of the parsley (save some for garnish) and the garlic.
Add 2 teaspoons of salt, if desired.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Strain and discard pulp (but save the broth).
Let the chicken cool enough to handle, then remove the skin.
Tear the meat from the bones and cut into pieces about the size of a half dollar.

title: classic glorified chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Meanwhile, in 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side up.
Drizzle with margarine.
A dash of Italian seasoning in the margarine is very tasty, too.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: my three in one cookies(chocolate chip, peanut butter and oatmeal cookies)
directions: Cream together butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Also add eggs plus peanut butter. Blend until creamy.
Add all the dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture, gradually.
Then stir in chocolate chips.
Place cookie dough onto plastic wrap and roll.
Chill until you are ready to bake the cookies.
Slice cookie dough and bake at 375° for 8 minutes for chewy cookies.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies. You may also freeze this cookie dough if you don't use it all.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all liquid ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer until melted.

title: jimmy dean dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until vegetables are slightly tender.
Add rest of ingredients. Serve warm with corn chips.

title: pork chops special
directions: Tenderize pork chops; salt, pepper and flour them.
Fry along with potatoes and onions until they are brown.
Drain oil.
Pour tomatoes and juice over ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Add a little water, if necessary.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Arrange in layers in the order given.
Sprinkle frozen peas (do not cook) over the first 4 ingredients.
Spread salad dressing over peas.
Sprinkle sugar; then sprinkle grated cheese over this. Fry bacon crisp, then drain and break into pieces and sprinkle over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and put in large bowl with green onions, celery and celery seed.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp. Do not drain.
Add flour gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vinegar, water and sugar, stirring until smooth. Immediately pour mixture over potatoes and mix well.

title: pepperoni caesar salad
directions: In small bowl, combine the oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, garlic, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; set aside.
In a large salad bowl, combine romaine and pepperoni.
Drizzle with dressing; sprinkle with croutons and Parmesan.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in baking dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada supreme
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Dip tortillas in hot broth.
Place on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add layer of chicken, onion and cheese, then repeat: tortillas, chicken, onion and cheese until pan is filled.

title: taco chicken
directions: Put egg, water and chicken in large bowl.
In large plastic bag, put seasonings and chips and chicken, shake until well coated. Put on pan, sprayed with cooking oil.
Bake, uncovered, 12 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Bake at 400°.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat together brown sugar, eggs and vegetable oil.
Mix in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Continue beating until mixture is well mixed.
Spread in 9 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Cut into bars.

title: tuna-potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Add margarine and onions. Cover until margarine has melted.
Add eggs, mayonnaise, pimiento and tuna.
Stir to mix.
Serve warm.

title: bean taco dip
directions: Mix together and cook 10 minutes.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine egg, orange juice and oil.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts. Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes, until done.
Remove from pan in 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: potato latkes
directions: Pare and grate potatoes into mixing bowl.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Grate in onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except shortening.
Melt shortening in heavy pan.
Drop batter by spoonful and fry until brown and crisp on both sides.
Serve with sour cream, applesauce or cinnamon and sugar.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados and tomatoes together.
Add everything else and mix well.

title: stir and roll pastry
directions: Dry ingredients into medium sized bowl, pouring oil and milk (in same measuring cup) but don't stir.
Add all at once to flour mix and stir lightly with fork.
Place 1/2 of dough between two squares of wax paper.
Rol dough from center to edge in all directions.
Carefully peel off top paper.
Any dough which tears can be easily mended by pressing edges together without moistening.
Lift pastry and bottom paper together.
Place pastry, with paper side up, into 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
After filling has been added then add top pastry the same way.
Proceed with recipe directions for your pie.

title: lime chicken
directions: Mix together soy sauce, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, mustard and pepper.
Place chicken in a bowl and pour over all.
Cover and marinate 30 minutes or more.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Spray frypan with butter flavored cooking spray and heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken and cook for 6 to 7 minutes on each side or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Lid can be placed over frying pan part of the time.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour with sugar, soda and salt. Beat eggs in bowl until thick and lemon colored. Add undrained fruit. Stir in dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it tests done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat water to boiling; add broccoli and cook about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage with onions
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Drain; fry onions in butter until light brown.
Add to cabbage mix.
Good with noodles.

title: upside-down chili pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in melted Swift'ning.
Add beans, seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover.
Simmer gently about 15 minutes. Pour into a deep 9-inch pie plate rubbed with Swift'ning.
Top with cornbread batter.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for 20 minutes.
To serve, cut pie shaped pieces.

title: eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan or dish, layer graham crackers. Mix pudding and sweet milk. Beat with hands or mixer until thick. Fold in cool whip and mix well. Pour over crackers in pan. Holding crackers in hand cover with chocolate frosting. The place on top of pudding mix until all is covered. Chill over night

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut chicken into medium shrimp sized pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt oleo in a saucepan over low heat; add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat 2 minutes, then pour over chicken.
Bake in preheated oven 10 minutes at 350°. Separate chicken pieces and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Have enough spaghetti cooked for 2 and when chicken removed from oven push to side and stir in cooked spaghetti.
Eat and enjoy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine cheese, corn, celery, onion and cracker crumbs; stir in the eggs, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley if desired.

title: oriental spaghetti
directions: Precook linguini.
Add a little oil and let stand in refrigerator,
In a large frypan or wok, cook the pork strips slowly.
When pork is thoroughly cooked, add celery, onions and green peppers.
Toss and cook briefly, the vegetables must stay crisp.
Reduce heat and add linguini, soy sauce and garlic powder. Toss until all ingredients are well mixed and linguini is heated thoroughly.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and orange jello.
Blend in cottage cheese. Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix pineapple and oranges in Cool Whip mixture.
Cool for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots just until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add carrots. Stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Serve cold as a salad or warm it and use as a side dish. Store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Yields 8 cups.

title: apple crunch
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in egg.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix box of confectioners sugar with 1/2 cup water and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme.
Stir into mixture.
Add peanut butter and stir until thickens.
Grease plate with butter.
Pour candy into plate.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Serve.

title: crabmeat cream cheese spread
directions: Cream cream cheese and spread on serving dish.
Spread meat on top, then spread sauce on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: refreshing drink
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Melt together oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in greased iron skillet.
Press in cheese with fork.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham cheese cubes
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Spread on ham slices and stack.
Freeze 2 hours.
Remove and cube 1 hour before serving. Put a toothpick in the center of each cube.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Flour and pan-fry chicken until golden brown.
Add all other ingredients to soup.
Place chicken in a glass baking dish and pour mushroom mixture over the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Cook cranberries following package directions until they all pop open.
Cool completely.
Drain juice from fruit and mix fruit into cooled cranberries.
Add more or a little less fruit to taste.
Make extra.
This is a hit at holiday dinners!

title: crabby-appleton salad
directions: If you use potatoes, boil first.
If you don't use the potatoes, be boiling the eggs while mixing the other ingredients together.
Let potatoes cool before adding to the other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add sugar and set aside.
Beat eggs; then beat in oil and vanilla. Add flour mixture; then apple slices and nuts.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Very good.

title: levane's pound cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar once.
Put oleo in mixing bowl and cream. Add about 2 tablespoons of flour and mix.
Add 1/2 sugar, mix, add other 1/2 sugar and mix.
Add eggs one at a time alternately with flour.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Cook until golden brown on 350° (about 1 hour).

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cool, cut in half and scoop out pulp.
Set aside.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour, stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute stirring constantly.
Gradually add 6 cups milk. Cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, 1/2 green onions, 1/2 bacon bits, 1 cup of cheese.
Cook until heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if needed.
Garnish with onions, bacon, and cheese.

title: pork chops sparado
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In large skillet over medium heat, rub fat over bottom of skillet to grease well.
Discard fat.
Add chops and brown well on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add the shallots, vermouth or chicken broth and rosemary (if dried).
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, or until pork is tender. Remove chops and skim fat.
If using fresh rosemary, sprinkle over chops now.
Then spoon pan juices over chops.

title: spanish sausage and black bean soup(soaked overnight)
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Drain and set aside. Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Add sausage and cook until done. Drain sausage on paper towels and set aside. Reserve drippings in Dutch oven. Add ham, onions, carrots, green bell pepper, garlic, pepper, thyme, cumin and bay leaf to reserved drippings in Dutch oven; saute 5 minutes. Thinly slice reserved sausage. Add sausage, reserved beans, undiluted chicken broth and 7 cups water to Dutch oven, stirring well. Bring to a boil. Partially cover. Reduce heat and simmer 3 1/2 hours or until beans are very tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in sherry and parsley. Simmer over medium heat, partially covered, an additional 30 minutes. Enjoy it!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and beat until creamy the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, butter, milk, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla (optional).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix first six ingredients to make cornbread.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Boil chicken in plenty of water for broth. Mix this with other ingredients and put in a greased pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 450°.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar, add pumpkin and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, add to creamed mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake.
Boil crushed pineapple with sugar for 2 minutes. Pour hot mixture over baked cake; cool.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour over cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip in which coconut and nuts have been mixed.
Refrigerate cake.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix and boil for 1 minute the oleo, cocoa, sugar and milk. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper or shape as you like.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies, according to size.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Remove from pan after 15 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: italian baked frittata
directions: In 10-inch ovenproof skillet, over medium high heat, cook broccoli, mushrooms, red pepper and onion in margarine, until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients and cool.
Add remaining ingredients, chopped finely, and chill in 2-quart molds.

title: crullers
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, shortening, milk, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add flour and baking powder to mixture.
With floured hand, roll a tablespoon of dough 4-inches long.
Drop into hot oil until lite brown, turning once.
Drain on brown paper bag.
Roll into powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper; drain. Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart pan with crushed chips. Mix meat, beans, soup and tomatoes. Pour over chips. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh tomato aspic
directions: Cut
tomatoes
in
small pieces over a bowl, conserving and using
all
the liquid.
Add celery, green pepper, garlic juice and
cream cheese, broken in pieces.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to it sufficient hot water to make 1/4 cup to
dissolve the gelatin.
Add to tomato mixture.
Add mayonnaise.
Season
to taste
with
salt and pepper; pour into an oiled quart size mold. Serves 8 to 10.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden; cool completely.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Heat 2 1/2 cups of bouillon to boiling point.
Drop balls into broth; cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: brunch pizza squares
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Unroll crescent rolls into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Press dough 1/2-inch up the sides and seal seams. Sprinkle with sausage.

title: zucchini parmesan bread
directions: Mix flour, zucchini, sugar, cheese, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Melt butter.
Stir in buttermilk.
(If you don't have buttermilk, measure 2 tablespoons vinegar into a cup and add milk to make 1 cup.)
Add eggs and onion.

Mix until smooth, then stir into flour mixture just until mixed (mixture may seem dry). Spread in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and loaf pulls away from sides of pan. Cool on rack.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cereal, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small bowl, blend milk, sugar, egg and margarine until smooth.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture just until moistened.
Mix in apple.
Spoon batter into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups almost full. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a paste with the oil and flour in a pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the shrimp.
Simmer for about an hour.
Add the shrimp and simmer until shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: In large bowl, mix corn, red onion, green pepper and parsley. In small bowl, whisk together sour cream and broth.
Add vinegar; whisk to blend.
Whisk in mayonnaise; beat until light and frothy. Toss cream mixture, salt and pepper with vegetable mixture. Chill.
When ready to serve, garnish with tomato, bacon and green onion.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Mix by stirring.
Do not beat or use mixer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tested done.
Use a large pan.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop and mix together in large bowl. Serve with chips.

title: frontier chowder
directions: In a large, heavy pot, brown the beef over medium heat, stirring, until beef loses its pinkness.
Stir in the chili powder and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in the bean with bacon soup, cream of tomato soup, water, tomatoes and corn.
Heat to simmering; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with chopped, fresh parsley for garnishing, if desired.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in next four ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.

title: walnut chicken
directions: In medium mixing bowl, mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Stir in chicken and coat well.
Set aside.
In large skillet, heat 4 tablespoons oil.
In medium saucepan, mix 2 cups water and chicken bouillon; heat until dissolved.
Let cool.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine soups and sauce; stir to mix well.
In oblong baking dish, place tortillas on bottom.
Pour 1/2 sauce mixture on top, then 1/2 chicken and 1/2 chopped onion.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare crust.
Heat oven.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.
Mix ingredients and pour into crust.

title: 50's tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles; drain.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter. Add dates and nuts. Knead together. Form into balls. Melt chips together and dip balls in. Cool on wax paper.

title: dave's crock-pot bean soup
directions: Soak kidney and white beans overnight; drain.
Brown turkey. Put beans, chicken broth, turkey and onions in crock-pot.
Bring to boil on high; cook on low all day.
Add lima beans; return to high heat for 45 minutes, or until limas are done.
Add water as required to compensate for moisture boiled off.

title: spicy christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in oats.
Roll out on a floured board.
Not too much flour.
Cut into Christmas shapes. Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice skillet
directions: Brown chicken in oil, then season with salt and pepper.
Add sauce mix, water, tomatoes and rice, stirring together thoroughly. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peas and pimientos.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: bacon wraps(appetizers)
directions: Blend cream cheese, sausage and parsley.
Set aside.
Trim crust from bread and cut each slice down the middle.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread (put plenty but not so much that you can't roll the bread up).
Roll bread in a jelly roll fashion.
Take one slice of bacon and cut in half (very diagonally).
Take half of slice of bacon and wrap around ball; secure with a toothpick. Freeze or bake at 350° until crust lightly browns.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Pour over popcorn.
Form balls the size you like.
Melt caramels and water; coat popcorn balls.

title: wild plum tea
directions: Steep boiling water and tea bags for 5 minutes.
Boil sugar and 2 quarts water 5 minutes.
Stir last mixtures into tea and water mixtures.
Serve hot or cold with orange slices.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until everything is moist. Pour into a greased and floured cake pan (Bundt or oblong cake). Test after baking for 45 minutes, usually takes about 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in 13-inch baking pan.
Dump pineapple tidbits on top.
Pour cake mix on top; spread evenly (dry cake). Dump chopped pecan nuts.
Dump coconut on top.
Pour melted butter over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole bowl.

title: coffee brownies
directions: Heat brown sugar and butter in saucepan until butter melts. Dissolve coffee in hot water and add to mixture.
Cook.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread mixture into a greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: grilled herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
In heavy foil, place 1 ear of corn. Add 2 tablespoons of margarine mixture.
Seal each ear separately. Grill 10 to 15 minutes, turning, until corn is tender.

title: no bake sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: In small bowl, blend Equal with evaporated milk.
Add egg, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Blend and set aside.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Blend in milk mixture.
Continue stirring over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened; about 5 minutes. Blend in pumpkin.
Turn into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish if desired with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt according to package directions; drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and peanuts.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onions; mix well.
Melt butter and pour over crumbs.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook syrup, oleo and sugar in a 2-quart saucepan to boiling.
Boil gently uncovered 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Place pecans in pie crust.
Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: beef stew ala king
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pan; let stand for 30 minutes.
Cook slowly for about an hour and 30 minutes or until meat becomes tender.
Add water to sauce if it becomes too thick. Serve over rice or noodles.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: liver pate
directions: Chop celery and onions.
Saute liver, celery, onions, and margarine.
Take out with slotted spoon.
Add eggs and chop until smooth, can use blender to get smooth.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Place above ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Grease and flour the bread pans; fill pans a little over 1/2 full.)

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with lemonade, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Coarsely grate the zucchini.
Spread grated zucchini on a towel and allow to dry for about 20 minutes.
Place chopped scallions in a bowl and crumble in feta cheese.
Stir in chopped parsley and mint, dried mint and paprika.
Add flour to mixture and season well with salt and pepper.
Gradually add the beaten eggs and mix thoroughly before stirring in the drained, grated zucchini.
Batter will be lumpy.
Heat a few tablespoons of oil in a large frying pan and drop heaping spoonsful of the mixture into the hot oil.
Flatten the cakes down with the back of a spoon. Cook the cakes for about 2 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.
Chop limes and spritz fritters with lime juice before serving.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.

title: ann's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Beat egg yolk and add small amount of mixture.
Return to pot and cook until thick.
Remove from heat, add salt and vanilla and pour into baked pie crust.
Add meringue. Bake until brown.

title: sour cream fudge chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients, except chips, 5 minutes in mixer.
Fold in chips; pour into greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: chicken-cabbage dinner salad
directions: Pour dressing on salad.
Toss and refrigerate for at least a few hours.
Tastes better everyday.
A complete meal.

title: yankee sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Evenly arrange half of sweet potatoes in shallow, 1 1/2-quart, microwave-safe pan.
Top with all apple slices.
Layer remaining sweet potatoes over apples; reserve.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat the olive oil in a 10-quart pot; add the onions, garlic, carrots, celery and half the salt.
Cook over low heat until the onions are wilted, but not browned.
Add the cabbage, kale, thyme, bay leaves and the rest of the salt.
Increase the heat and cook for a minute, stirring constantly.
Add the water, tomatoes and chickpeas and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add the pasta and cook 15 minutes more or until the pasta is tender.
Correct the seasoning with salt and pepper. Serve with good bread and butter or garlic oil.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Looks and tastes like pecan pie.

title: banana trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl or deep glass bowl, crumble a layer of crushed vanilla wafers; then add a layer of sliced bananas.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions and add condensed milk, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread a layer of pudding mixture over the wafers and bananas.
Continue this procedure until the size you want is made, ending with pudding on top.
Grate vanilla wafers and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate leftover pudding for individual servings as needed.

title: radical reese's balls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls. Chill overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together.
Dip preformed balls into the chocolate.
Let them harden.

title: frosting cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then stir in coconut frosting. Add pecans.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour until done.

title: pork pineapple bake
directions: Cut pork luncheon meat slightly more than halfway through loaf into 8 sections.
Place pork in ungreased baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon mustard between every other cut.
Insert half slice pineapple in each cut; top with remaining half slice pineapple. Insert whole cloves in pineapple, if desired.
Sprinkle brown sugar over pork.
Cook in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits(yummy bites)
directions: Combine butter and sour cream. Put the flour into a large bowl and pour butter and sour cream into it.
Stir to mix well. Fill ungreased mini muffin tin with 1 heaping tablespoonful of batter in each cup. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Cool for about 3 minutes before removing from pan.
Good with roast beef or ham in them.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients with one cup of nuts, then roll "ball" in one cup of nuts.
Make in different designs, like "snowman" etc.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Use a large bowl for mixing.
Mix pudding and milk at low speed.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add lemon juice to taste.
Slice bananas into pudding. Crumble cookies into this.
Save a little of cookie crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
I use sugar free pudding.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef until tender; add remaining ingredients and cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.
To give this more body, cooked white beans or macaroni may be added.
A can of mixed vegetables may be added if desired.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with last package of cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: canned peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish in oven.
Mix together all the dry ingredients then stir in the milk. Stir in about half of the melted oleo.
Pour into the dish with the rest of the oleo. Arrange peaches over this and pour the peach juice over it all. Bake at 325° until crust rises to top and browns, about 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Beat eggs lightly and add vanilla flavoring, buttermilk and Crisco oil.
Beat just a few seconds together.
Add mashed bananas to egg mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and fold in egg mixture until all flour is gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).
Makes one regular size Banana Bread.

title: mexican franks
directions: Slice wieners (round wise).
Put in skillet using low heat. Add onion, tomato sauce and chilies.
Stir together and simmer for a couple of minutes.
Add mayonnaise to the mixture.
Spoon into buns and top with cheese.
Place in oven and melt cheese.

title: dolores' carrot souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil, add carrots and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and mash the carrots.
To the carrots add melted butter, sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla extract and beaten eggs.
Mix well and transfer to a 2 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake in a preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Brown sausage and turkey and drain well.
Beat eggs, milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add meat.
Pour into pie crust.
Add cheese; pat down with spoon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done to touch.

title: marinated barbecue baby drumsticks
directions: Separate chicken wings into 3 pieces; discard tips.
Mix remaining ingredients for marinade.
Marinate chicken pieces for 2 hours, turning once.
Bake at 350° on a rack in uncovered shallow pan for 1 hour, turning once.
Baste 4 times with marinade.
Serve with Chinese mustard.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Roll out in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Take a fork; push down, then across, making fork prints on cookie dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, powdered sugar and oleo well.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and eggs.
Cream these with the previous ingredients.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Alternate with flour mixture 1 cup of salad oil and mix all ingredients together.
Chill well. Make into balls rolled in sugar and flatten the balls dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a large heavy saucepan. Cook slowly, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda; stir slightly.
Pour evenly into a well-greased shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Cool partially by lifting edges with knife; when firm, turn the entire slab of brittle.
When cold, break into pieces.
Store at once in an airtight container.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and put 1 stack Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick margarine melted on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use in place of salt and pepper on everything.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions.
Add pineapple juice. Just before serving, add scoops of sherbet and ginger ale.
For red punch, use raspberry Kool-Aid and sherbet.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer for at least an hour or more and it's ready to eat.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add barbecue sauce, onion, salt, celery seed, mustard, molasses, beans and mushrooms to ground beef. Stir well.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Serve hot, or cool and freeze for later use.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in an electric mixer until creamy with no lumps.

title: tangy slaw
directions: In a large bowl toss first 5 ingredients.
In large measuring cup mix together vinegar, sugar and cooking oil.
Pour over slaw and toss.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving, tossing to mix vinegar dressing with slaw 2 to 3 times before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: baked cheese potato slices
directions: Mix soup, paprika, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Arrange potatoes in 2-quart baking dish (overlapping potatoes).
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; spoon soup mixture over the cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: mom's peanut butter icing
directions: Cook until a soft ball forms in water.
(Stir occasionally as it cooks.) Take from heat. Add vanilla.
Beat with spoon until the icing loses its shine. Spread on cake.
This is good on any chocolate cake.

title: moretti's peanut butter bars
directions: Put butter, sugar and Karo into a pan and bring to a full boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat; add peanut butter and vanilla and mix.
Pour over cereal and stir until coated.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and press to set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 of stuffing into pan.
Cook broccoli until separated.
Drain.
Layer broccoli over stuffing.
Mix soup and milk together and pour 1/2 over broccoli. Repeat with more stuffing, broccoli and soup.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with parsley and butter.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: cherry-apple whip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: perch dinner
directions: Mix first three ingredients and dip fillets into milk; let stand.
When fillets are dry, roll in dry mixture and pan-fry in cooking oil.
